beer.beer_description: Barrel aged dark sour with blackberry and vanilla

Das Kultbier seit Generationen.

Der Geschmack ist vollmundig mit milder Hopfennote und ausgeprägter Malz-aromatik. Hochwertiges bayerisches Malz, Hopfen aus der Hallertau, bester Aromahopfen aus Tettnang am Bodensee und die behutsame Gärung geben dem Flötzinger Hell seinen einzigartigen Geschmack.

Ein Bier mit milder Persönlichkeit.
Imperial Stout aged in bourbon barrels with Chocolate

beer.beer_name: Double Dip Bourbon Barrel Aged Imperial Stout
beer.beer_description: Bourbon Barrel Aged Imperial Stout aged in Driftless Glen Bourbon Barrels

beer.beer_name: Double Dip Rye Whiskey Barrel Aged Imperial Stout
beer.beer_description: Rye Whiskey Barrel Aged Imperial Stout aged in Driftless Glen Rye Barrels
Belgian-inspired Imperial Stout.

The brewer's daughter Marie Hausbrendel from Jakobervorstadt spoiled her guests with fresh beer as early as the Roaring Twenties. Now grandson Leopold Schwarz has dedicated his own beer to his grandmother: the new Schwarzbräu "Marie Hausbrendel" pampers with a pleasantly fresh and mature taste.
Lychee, grapefruit zest
Teddy grahams, werther's caramel
This 7.0% medium-bodied, coffee-colored Baltic Porter carries the flavors of Madagascar vanilla and Mexican cinnamon with the aromatics of dark Oaxacan chocolate.

beer.beer_name: Oak Barrel Aged Flanders Red Ale
beer.beer_description: We’re pleased to announce the release of our Oak Barrel Aged Flanders Red Ale! This beer showcases our blend of a young Flanders Red aged for 24 months in American Oak barrels, resulting in a beer which greets the drinker with aromatics of sangiovese grapes and American Oak alongside flavors of tart cherry and rhubarb.
Mango, habanero, apple, and honey - time to get freaky! Not too hot - but just the right spice.

Sidle up to the perfect pint pub for an innovative new deliciously smooth, dark and indulgent classic-style milk stout, but with a tasty dairy-free almond milk twist. All of the flavor and mouthfeel of a bold tasting stout, yet lighter-better-faster, with a nod to the new non-dairy day dawning.

Minutiae 2021 is composed of casks as young as 12 months and as old as 30 months, filled with six different base stouts. Nutty, dark chocolate, 
with layers of smoke, char, and leather.
Special one off beer.  This is a special version of Vlad Russian Imperial Stout that is Bourbon Barrel Aged.

This sour treat is a blended (cuvée) of peach lambic and geuze aged in wood barrels for 5 months. With a base of pilsner malt and local raw wheat we added over 1000 lbs of peaches 
from Herman’s Orchard Farm in St. Charles and aged hops during a secondary fermentation.

beer.beer_name: Big Board Nut Brown - Imperial (Bourbon Barrel Aged)
beer.beer_description: Aged in bourbon barrels
Summer selection 2012
O.H.S.O. Gilbert - This decadent German Chocolate Cake Stout was brewed lactose-free before resting 8 months in barrel and finished on fresh toasted coconut, pecans, and cacao.

Inspired by the classic fizzy lager and shot specials enjoyed at corner bars everywhere, a base Helles Bock starts out quite plain to maximize contributions from its time in bourbon barrels. The final beer is a blend of freshly used bourbon barrels, second use barrels, as well as fresh beer. During aging, Beer for Burgers picks up notes of coconut, vanilla, alcoholic heat, and roasted wood tannins. Like a beer and a shot special, this beer is ever changing. The barrel stock changes as well as the blend. The goal is not to make the same beer over and over again, rather to maximize the flavors coming out of the barrels as they are… and make sure it tastes like a beer and shot you’d get with your burger.

Farmhouse saison brewed with barley, wheat, and rye. Fermented and conditioned in oak with a mixed culture containing brett and saison yeast. Dry hopped with whole cone Ekuanot hops. FOBAB Gold 2017 Wild Beer/Brett

beer.beer_name: A Wee Bit Foggy Scotch Ale
beer.beer_description: "True to the traditional Wee Heavy Scotch Ale style, A Wee Bit Foggy bursts with the rich flavors of carmelized malt and dried fruit and finishes slightly sweet with a hint of nuttiness.
Imperial Breakfast Stout with coffee, vanilla, and maple syrup.

Das original Kurpfalzbräu Helles schmeckt süffig und löscht den Durst. Traditionell gebraut in der Kurpfalz. Hellgelbes, klares, untergäriges Bier mit fester Schaumkrone. Im Antrunk bestimmt von einer feinen Malznote, am Gaumen begleitet von einer dezenten Bittere.
Contract-brewed at Egerer.
Bayerisches Vollbier

Pistachio Deluxe is an Imperial Stout brewed with pistachio. A decadent dessert beer packed with notes of rich fudge, cake batter and pistachio, making for an ideal post-dinner sipper to send off the night.

A dark, malty celebration ale with layered flavors and beautifully balanced hopping. Jubelale pours deep garnet in color, medium bodied, with notes of chicory, earth, spice and fruit. To beer lovers, it’s like Yule fire and family.

Heineken is a 5% ABV euro pale lager, made by Heineken International since 1873. It is available in a 4.3% alcohol by volume, in countries such as Ireland. It is the flagship product of the company and is made of purified water, malted barley, hops, and yeast. In 1886 H. Elion finished the development of the Heineken A-yeast. This is the yeast that is still used for the beer. The beer is force carbonated. It is popular in the United States, Europe and Middle Eastern countries.

beer.beer_name: Victoria Celebra Dia De Los Muertos

beer.beer_description: The processing of high-quality malt from own barley cultivation, exquisite hops qualities and fresh spring brewing water from the nature reserve Sieseberg give this noble Pils a special freshness and its round, fine-dry taste. For over 315 years, the Schloßbrauerei Rheder is owned by the barons of Spiegel and Mengersen. It is located in the outer bailey of Rheder Castle. In 1830, the brewery was expanded for the first time and converted into a steam brewery based on the Bavarian model. Now, the lower-fermented beer, which is easier to store and transport, can be brewed.
Belgian Abbey Ale
ABV varies. 5.1% and 5.4%

First Pils is the first beer ever brewed by Hopewell and, fittingly, the one we reach for most often. A Pilsner-style Lager with a bready malt profile and a snappy noble hop finish. Tastes great anytime—but best with friends.
Our annual Black Gold aged instead in Rye whiskey barrels

Aged in Elijah Craig 14yr barrels resulting in a rich and complex stout with a very intricate palate.

A true expression of beer and barrel makes for a decadent, one of a kind experience

Introducing Barrel Aged LUX #13 American Strong Ale. The first release in our 2021 Barrel Aged Series, and also our 13,000 batch of beer back in 2015.

LUX #13 features notes of caramel, marshmallow, and melted toffee all blended together with a lingering finish from aging in oak bourbon barrels for 12 months.

This is Dovetail’s second season of Framboise. 2020 is a 13-barrel blend of spontaneously-fermented and traditionally-made beer from 2017 and 2018, that then spent 7 months on nearly 700kg of red raspberries
Black Gold aged in Rye barrels.

A combination of Branch and Bone and our saison yeasts. Open fermented and mellowed for over a month. More subdued wild yeast than our regular house saisions. Also more malt forward. Light apricot or peach notes but very in the mix and balanced. Medium bodied with almost a disappearing finish with a touch of lingering dryness or minerality. Very quaffable.
Burbon barrel aged

beer.beer_name: Big Beer Little Can Barrel Aged Marzen
beer.beer_description: Limited Release
Aged in one five gallon whisky cask.

A Belgian-style Dark Strong Ale brewed with a touch of molasses.  Aged in rare Caroni rum barrels resulting in a round, malty profile with notes of oak, spice, rich cane sugar, dark dried fruits and all the complexity of a very well aged rum.
A blend of 3 spontaneous ales and ciders.
Imperial nut brown aged six months in New Holland Zeppelin Bend whisky barrels

The term cuvée is used in both the wine and beer worlds, most often to delineate specially blended batches from the absolute best barrels or tanks the vintner or brewer has to offer. That is certainly the case with our Cuvée; each barrel for this blend was selected from a variety of base beers, barrel types, and fermentation cultures to produce a wild ale that is greater than the sum of its parts. Aromas of ripe pineapple and fresh hay give way to layers of jammy grapes, oak tannins, bright acidity, sweet malts, and waves of funk and stone fruit flavors. Bottle conditioned to continue to develop and mature over time, this unique blend is one of the most complex beers we’ve ever produced and we’re proud to label it as our Cuvée.

Inland Seas Series. 

Brewed with Michigan tart cherries.
Clean and crisp with citrus accents.

Moving up the hop-chain from our Pale Ale, this insanely hopped beer features copious amounts of columbus and cascade hops. Floral, Piney, Citrusy – it’s all there and more making a hop head’s delight.

Dunkles untergäriges Bock-Bier

Ein Sondersud, der exklusiv für den Kalea Bieradventskalender eingebraut wurde.

This Belgian-style Holiday Ale combines the beloved flavor profile of Golden Monkey with notes of cranberry, orange peel, cinnamon and nutmeg to deliver a delightfully smooth finish, perfect for merry gatherings with family and friends.

For the second year in a row, Proprietor’s Bourbon County Stout is inspired by a classic frozen treat and brewed again by the mastermind, Emily Kosmal. A flavor house specialist, Emily has the knowledge and skill to bring her dessert treats to life. Proprietor’s Bourbon County Stout is aged in bourbon barrels and blended with luscious strawberries, vanilla and coconut, reminiscent of a classic strawberry ice cream bar. These elements come together to create the indelible flavors of decadent shortcake, layered with vanilla and topped off with the slight fruitiness of strawberries, similar to the ice cream bar’s strawberry core.

For the first time ever, we’re digging into the Proprietor’s (Chicago-only release) vault and bringing back a fan favorite with Bourbon County Fourteen Stout. But this time, it’s with a twist. We’re paying homage to the popular Proprietor’s 2014 recipe, but upping the rye ante by adding rye to the mash bill. Layering cassia bark, cocoa nibs, panela sugar, and coconut water, this stout has an intricate, sweet and spicy flavor profile that will have fans going back sip after sip

beer.beer_name: Bourbon County Brand Classic Cola Stout (2021)
Bourbon County Double Barrel Brand Toasted Barrel Stout (2021)
beer.beer_description: Our Double Barrel Toasted Barrel Stout was aged for one year in Elijah Craig’s Small Batch Bourbon Barrels, then another year in Elijah Craig Toasted Bourbon Barrels. In addition to the familiar chocolate, caramel, and vanilla comes flavors of toasted marshmallow and a very pronounced fruit and oak finish. Bourbon County Double Barrel Toasted Barrel Stout has a rich complexity and flavor only attainable through true craftsmanship, partnership, expert blending, and, of course, patience.

beer.beer_name: Bourbon County Brand Cherry Wood Stout (2021)
beer.beer_description: This year, we took wood complexities to another level by doing something we’ve never done before: we took fully-matured Bourbon County Stout and finished it with toasted fruitwood—specifically, honeycomb-shaped cherry wood chips. The versatility of the cherry wood and honeycomb shape allowed for maximum flavor extraction, revealing complex characteristics like red fruit, ripe cherry, and light toffee, which are not found in the original oak barrel itself. The result is an amazing elevation and a notable difference from our Original Bourbon County Stout.

beer.beer_name: Bourbon County Brand Reserve Blanton’s Stout (2021)
beer.beer_description: We partnered with our friends at Blanton’s and aged our Imperial Stout for 18 months in barrels from one of the world’s most sought-after bourbons—Blanton's Original Single Barrel Bourbon. Taken from the center-cut or middle sections of the famous Warehouse H, Blanton’s Original Single Barrel was once only available for ambassadors, dignitaries, and friends of the Blanton family, but now is available for everyone to enjoy. Just as we set the standard for barrel-aged stouts, Blanton’s set the standard for single barrel bourbons. Through our partnership, we created a truly unique reserve filled with rich dark chocolate and oak notes, finished with warm aromatics of baking spices such as clove, nutmeg, and cinnamon.

Our Bourbon County Reserve 150 Stout is aged for one year in Old Forester’s 150th Anniversary Bourbon Barrels. Expect barrel-forward flavor with notes of chocolate, vanilla, and coconut, followed with molasses, almond, berry, and oak.

Our rich imperial stout is blended from a mix of bourbon barrels from distilleries such as Heaven Hill, Wild Turkey, and Buffalo Trace, each aged in freshly emptied bourbon barrels for 8-14 months. Expect flavors of chocolate and vanilla, oak, whiskey, and molasses, followed by caramel, berry fruit, and almond.

As the days get shorter, Lady Liberty glows at our sunset gate with her welcoming arms. A light and refreshing straw-colored beer, fruity and sweet, brewed with real mango's, brimming with tropical floral notes. You’ll feel transported to an oasis during the orange and red leaves of fall.
Collaboration with Fannie's - Stout brewed with Chocolate Cake & Lactose & aged in CH Distillery Bourbon Barrels for 9 Months.

"Northeast meets middle east by way of Kentucky.” We recently discovered a recipe for Maple Bourbon Baklava, and after countless attempts at buttering phyllo, we decided to scrap the pastry and make it a beer instead. Big maple and bourbon aroma support the rich powerhouse combination of pecan, whiskey, and sweet honey malt flavors. All of the sensory experience of decadent baklava, minus the sticky fingers.

Malt
Pilsner, Cara 300, Simpson Dark, Carafa 3, Oats, Wheat, Pils, Vienna 

Hops
Columbus 18

Adjuncts 
Bourbon Barrels 8-12 months

Pecan
Maple
Aged 100 days in bourbon barrels.

beer.beer_name: Imperial Cookies n Cream Jones Dog
beer.beer_description: Imperial Stout Ale with cookie wafers, vanilla, cacao nibs and lactose.

This bright golden Saison is a blend of fresh and wood-aged Classic from our American white oak foeders. On the nose, you'll catch enticing and balanced aromas of moderate Brett funk, fruit, and spicy notes of clove, nutmeg, and coriander. A taste reveals a smack of acidity composed with notes of vanilla, spice, apricot, and toasted bread.

1851 bezogen die 8. Husaren die Garnison in Paderborn und Neuhaus. Deren Rittmeister und Brauereibesitzer Adolph von Spiegel ist Namensgeber unseres Husaren Trunks. Ebenso wie der Rittmeister war, so ist auch unser Husaren Trunk ein echtes Original. Sein süffiger, vollmundiger Geschmack verbindet sich harmonisch mit einer leichten Bittere von reinem Aromahopfen. Unser Rittmeister hätte noch heute seine große Freude an dieser Spezialität.

The pleasant aroma of ginger greets you immediately as you lift this magenta magic to your lips. The ginger spice is complementary to the slight fruity-floral essence of the beer, a result of steeping whopping amounts of hibiscus flowers in the whirlpool just before fermentation. Light, crisp and refreshing, the perfect palate cleanser after any rich meal.

Malts: Pale, Wheat,Pilsner

Hops: Magnum

Adjuncts: Hibiscus, Ginger
Vintage 2015. Says so on the bottle.

Our Barleywine Ale features American and Belgian malts which provide the base of this extraordinary ale. After 12 months in bourbon barrels the award-winning Straight Jacket® emerges with notes of stone fruit, toasted coconut, molasses, and vanilla coming in waves as you swirl the glass. Enjoy now or store cold.

Behold, our original Barrel-aged Imperial Oatmeal Stout, Deth’s Tar, with hand-split whole vanilla beans. Flaked and malted oats lend a supremely silky body that belies the beer’s considerable strength. Pronounced vanilla flavor and aroma blends harmoniously with chocolatey caramel maltiness and blend of American & French oak. Enjoy now or store cold.

beer.beer_name: Very Special Old Flak Jacket - Single Barrel
beer.beer_description: A single Heaven Hill barrel of sweet component Barleywine and dry component Ryewine aged three years, plus a couple hosefuls of twice-barreled dry Barlewine, just as a treat. Cooked sugar, vanilla, and enough maple to warrant dual citizenship in Canada make an amicable ruckus before a prompt finish compliments of three years resting in American oak.

A blend of Jim Beam Distiller's Masterpiece Bourbon French oak PX Sherry finish-aged Stout and Barleywine, and two Vanilla Deth "money barrels," one dosed with three pounds of bourbon-soaked Papua New Guinea vanilla beans, and another stuffed with toasted Forêt de Tronçais French oak. Lumber-derived vanilla soars above a torrent of sweet caramel, date, and softened roast. Pinkies up, kiddos.

This bemusing, bepurpled curiosity is the result of blending double bourbon barrel-aged dry English Barleywine and an intrepid volume of unfermented blackberries. Restrained malt sweetness, hefty tannins, vanilla-laden American oak, and sweet, tart blackberry combine to make an “extreme” beer which retains a decidedly playful accessibility. Enjoy now or store cold.

Unblended sweet component Barleywine aged in a pair of sopping wet Great Lakes Distilling Rum barrels for three years. Familial expressions of malt sweetness and time resonate within a chasm beset by towering walls of barrel and spirit.
Berliner-style weisse beer with pumpkin and spices added after fermentation.
Imperial pastry stout.
Double Oak-aged English Barleywine. Viscous and rich, Clockwork was aged on cognac barrel staves before spending the winter in American oak bourbon barrels.

Official beer of Oswegoland's PrairieFest.

A slightly hazy, straw colored beer with low bitterness, and floral aromas from the hop additions. This is an excellent brew for the Summer nights while exploring all the offerings of the festival grounds.

A thick, milky-white stout with rich, textured body accented by Indonesian vanilla beans, Vietnamese cassia bark cinnamon & nutmeg all provided by our good friends at Epic Spices in Chicago. The result is a surprisingly balanced spiced beer reminiscent of delicious, mind-bending egg nog and holiday cookies of years gone by.
Sour Ale with Blueberries and Vanilla
Brewed with oatmeal cookies, lactose, raisins, chocolate, cinnamon, and vanilla. Brandy Barrel-Aged for 8 months.
Belgian Dubbel style ale barrel aged in Journeyman Road's End Rum barrels finished on fig and vanilla
Imperial Milk Stout with all natural peppermint, vanilla and cacao nibs

Re-inspired by a recent trip to Hawaii, came about. The recipe has come full-circle.  Over a decade of experience combining coconut and beer and brewing dark beers, we brewed Niu to be sort of a peek behind the curtain at Phase Three.  Big, adjuncted, dark beers are extremely labor intensive, involve a lot of planning and unfortunately, don’t offer a lot of drinkability.  Niu is 6.5%. It’s not meant to be a big pastry stout/porter, however it’s not small.  The base porter is light, but uses full-flavored UK malted grains, including Maris Otter, crystal malts and chocolate malts.  It’s rich, but refreshing.  It satisfies a dark, adjuncted beer craving but in a way where a pint of it is appropriate.

What’s better than Fall? Nothing’s better than Fall.  You think something’s better than fall?  Well you can pound sand as far as we’re concerned.  Fall is the time for football, quarter-zips, hoodies, and spiced beer.  We took a strong ale base and loaded it up with cinnamon sticks, nutmeg, and bitter orange peel to make a beer that is just so fitting for this time of year.

We miss our favorite pink beer, "Summerly," in the Winter, so we decided to brew a winterized wheat beer to take its place. "Dreamsicle Flurries" is a wheat beer with loads of orange juice and vanilla bean added. It tastes so good we forgot how much Winter sucks for a few minutes!
Mead and Bourbon Barrel Aged Russian Imperial Stout with Star Anise, Cinnamon, and Cocoa Nibs
A spiced cider featuring the flavors of fall: caramel, brown sugar, cinnamon, cardamom, and, of course, apples. Crisp as an autumn night with a long, but clean finish.

Lose control again with our semi-sweet blueberry mead—now aged in Hotel Tango Distillery’s Reserve Bourbon barrels and conditioned on 300 vanilla beans and 60 gallons of blueberries from Tillman Blueberry Farms.  Sweet blueberries and warming bourbon with a strong secondary note of vanilla.
Kings Orchard apple cider and wildflower honey fermented with champagne yeast.
Fresh Raspberry Spritzer Session Mead

A malty and robust Doppelbock Lager brewed with rich malts and noble hops. Expect warming notes of dark fruit and hoppy spice, and a finish with hints of toasted bread and toffee. A perfect beer to pair with a hearty winter meal.

beer.beer_name: Can You Pass the Acid Test?
beer.beer_description: Fermenter-soured ale with blackberries
An American brown ale with cacao nibs. Roasty malts and chocolaty flavors - what's not to love?

Inspired by coastal culture, Palm Shade combines the tropical fruit hop aroma of a modern IPA with the deeply quenching drinkability of a pale ale. Subtle hop bitterness with vibrant notes of mandarin orange, mango, and pineapple.
Inspired by Ponche, Mexico’s holiday fruit punch, this festive delight is cheerfully brewed with a touch of lactose and finished with tamarind, hibiscus, guava, currants, orange, and cinnamon.
A classic Porter rich with the delicious harmony of peanut butter. Open the top on this flavorful beer for a silky smooth drinking experience. No spoons required.
Inspired by the joy of live art and a bag of glazed almonds, Curbside Puppet Theater is a brown ale with honey-roasted almonds.
Cranberry, Apple & Cinnamon lightly carbonated session mead.
Smoothie style Dreamsicle mead with Coconut
The next in our Dungeon Master Series. This one is packed with Ancho Chile, Cacoa, Cinnamon & Vanilla.
Don't Worry, Be Gummy is double dry hopped with Mosaic, Citra and Ekuanot hops; giving this Hazy IPA a smooth feel with an array of complex flavors and aromas of melon, berry and citrus.
A truly unique cider! Made from Michigan Heritage apples, this 10% masterpiece will leave you warm inside. The aroma & taste is like freshly made apple sauce!
Modern style cider made the way the English make it.  Our Hard Apple has a well-balanced citrus and apple flavor. For those with more of a sweet tooth.

This beer, let us just say it encompasses the all. It pours a pillowed dense hazy golden yellow with a sense of mystery. Mosaic, Citra, and many beautiful hop things of Solera. There are many stories in Solemn Oath, but Behind All Things Are Reasons is a berry-propelled tropical fruit salad with mango, passion fruit, citrus, and pine at 6.5% ABV.

beer.beer_name: Harbor Country Delight (Blueberry Cheesecake, Pastry Sour)
beer.beer_description: Tart and fruity with a blueberry cheesecake flavor and a cloudy, red color. Hops: Horizon
Malt forward. Prunes, plums.

Brewed since 1994, our Black Chocolate Stout has itself become a modern classic, heralded the world over. It achieves its dark chocolate aroma and flavour through the artful blending of six malts and three distinct mashes.

beer.beer_name: Dragon’s Milk Reserve: Bourbon Barrel-Aged Stout With Salted Caramel (2021-3)
beer.beer_description: The final Reserve of 2021 is an ode to one of our favorite releases. Our latest legend is aged for three months in select bourbon barrels and layered with sweet and salty caramel flavors. The result is a truly indulgent brew best described as dessert in a glass.
Imperial stout with vanilla beans

beer.beer_name: Milk of the Murder Hornet - Gingerbread
beer.beer_description: Lactose IIPA with Gingerbread
Munich-style dunkel with American hops.
Fall season spiced wheat wine.

beer.beer_name: Barrel Aged Double Pecan Pie Brown Ale
beer.beer_description: Our bigger, more flavorful version of our Pecan Pie Brown barrel aged for 1 year in Willett Whiskey Barrels! Brewed with AZ Pecans, AZ Lactose, vanilla beans and maple syrup.
Double dry hopped DIPA with Galaxy, Citra, and Mosaic Cryo made in collaboration with our Roosevelt Row neighbors, The Theodore!

beer.beer_name: Don’t Funk It Up W Peaches

beer.beer_description: Say hey to Sun Day, your favorite sustainable hard seltzer. Produced entirely with energy from the Arizona sun, it’s filled with refreshing fruit flavors and weekend vibes. Whoever said there’s nothing new under the sun?
Little-known fact: Arizona grows some prime peaches. Our Peach Ale is made with the fruit for a crisp, enticing flavor as worthy of enjoying on a warm, sunny day as on a cool, refreshing night.
The Original Goose Island Bourbon County Brand Stout. Intense aromas of charred oak, vanilla, caramel, smoke.

beer.beer_name: Hey, Careful Man, There’s a Beverage Here!
beer.beer_description:
White Russian Imperial Stout

Wayout West there's this beer... Dear I wanna tell ya' about. Beer by the name Hey, careful man, there is a beverage here. Beer inspired by a certain dudes favorite potable, this imperial white milk stout is brewed with vanilla beans, and abideable amount of cacao Nibs and coldpressed coffee that really tied the beer together, did it not? It is the perfect oat soda for those days when you're out of your element and all you can do is say "f it, Dude, let's go bowling."
Imperial Stout with SPUTNIK Coffee and Maple Syrup

beer.beer_name: It'd Be A Lot Cooler If You Did (2021)
beer.beer_description: A barleywine aged in freshly dumped Woodford Reserve double oak barrels for 12 months
Kirin Ichiban Shibori is the name in the Japanese Market, whilst Kirin Ichiban is the name for export. 100% malt beer.
Rum Barrel-aged Gose with mango & hibiscus.

Come alive to crisp apple hard cider blended with the fresh taste of strawberries, soft and deep red, backed by mouth watering sweetness and a delicate hint of tartness. This is Strawberry Magic Hard Cider kicked up with a hint of Saturday night. We blend it a little differently around here. If you’ve never tried it, get ready for confetti.
It’s a big bad, spicy, chocolate bomb of a beer.

Witness the firepower of this fully operational Barrel-Aged Imperial Oatmeal Stout. Brewed with English specialty malts and the addition of flaked and malted oats to create a rich, chocolaty profile and silky mouthfeel that cloaks its considerable strength. The American oak barrels continue to build layers of complexity, reminiscent of vanilla, toasted coconut and caramel candy after aging this dark menace a full 12 months.

A weaponized quantity of freshly roasted whole bean coffee from Dark Matter Coffee Roasters imbues our Deth’s Tar Barrel-Aged Imperial Oatmeal Stout with assertive coffee aromatics without overshadowing the base beer on the palate. Pair with rich food or enjoy on its own. Keep cold. Enjoy now. We mean it.

This single Wild Turkey barrel of young, sweet component Deth’s Tar is infused with 25lbs of toasted coconut. Punchy American oak and bittersweet chocolate notes lay beneath a torrent of tropical bliss which becomes ever more pronounced as it warms.

Sweet component Deth's Tar aged two years in a single Weller Special Reserve barrel. Malty, graham laden, bittersweet chocolate mousse-esque, all tied together with a lovely spirit expression and restrained oak tannin.
Deth by Raspberries charged up with a healthy whap of Daydream Coffee light roast because we like a good time around here.

This all-too-drinkable fruited spin on Deth's Tar is equally at home in any setting. Aromas of roasted malt, American oak, bourbon, and fresh raspberry flesh emerge from the glass like a group hug for the nose while the palate is treated to a gentle sweetness and incisive acidity. Enjoy now or store cold.

Our Leipzig-style Gose and blueberries are a combination destined to be together, so we've done that for you with this edition of our Gose. The blueberries add another layer of fruity complexity to this sour ale already know for its tart, citrusy qualities while still balanced by the spicy character of coriander and a mineral-mouthfeel from French sea salt.

beer.beer_name: Wild Sour Series: Key Lime Pie Gose
beer.beer_description: We’ve added key lime, vanilla and lactose to our Leipzig-style gose to create a liquid version of the popular dessert. The result is a tart, creamy, refreshing treat for your tastebuds. Now, you can have your pie and drink it too.
Pilsner with jasmine, chamomile and iris
Oak aged vienna lager

With a little tip of the hat to our scientific, pioneering neighbors we created the innovative atom smasher limited run artisan beer. A heft, full-bodied lager reminiscent of Marzen beers from days gone by. However, this beer is aged in our oak foudres to add a complexity unmatched by the imported version of Oktoberfest beers today. Just add Ledersosen!

Meet the wild child, our tropical troublemaker with effervescent intentions. This ale pairs bright pineapple with apple and tart passionfruit in a sensual carimbo. Make the getaway, destination unknown, set off into sparkling skies. Let's get out of here. The possibilities, the thrill, the adventure; Wowie.

beer.beer_name: Magic Drip - Barrel-Aged Wheated Imperial Stout With Colombian Coffee
beer.beer_description:
Somewhere on the fringe of alchemy exists a fantastical marriage of magic and science. Behold this mystical blend of brewing –born from the binding of creativity and creation. Bold and beautiful, delivering doses of delight and delirium, it’s bound to put a spell on you.

Malts – Pale, Dark, Crystal, and Oats
Hops: Magnum
Adjuncts: Colombian Dark Roast from Messenger Coffee
 
Pair with an Old fashioned doughnut, raspberry cream cheese puff pastry, or stilton cheese, and have a delicious time.

The summer sun hits different where we're from. The warm rays are the hard-earned reward for our brutal winters, and we cherish them just a little bit more. Surly salutes those Invisible Rays with this tropical IPA full of pineapple and guava notes and just a kiss of lactose. Summer isn't endless here, but you'll wish this beer was.
Braced by bright grapefruit flavor and gentle tartness, this beer reigns supreme. Finishing crisp and citrusy, it sets a new standard for crushable.

A single-hop IPA brewed with Strata, a new hop from Oregon with aromas of passionfruit, grapefruit and wafting weed.

“He dwells on a great mountain. What use to call on him? Little he cares if men live or die. Better to be silent than to call his attention to you; he will send you dooms, not fortune!”
— Robert E. Howard

ABV 7.5% IBU 60

At long last, we bring you our take on a Hazy IPA.  It’s no secret that most of our portfolio is hop forward, flavorful, and unfiltered. With Barbarian Haze, we took the hopping protocol a bit further, using some new age brewing alchemy coupled with our old school heavy handed approach. Fans of the style will recognize the complex soft malt character that helps balance the generous hop additions for supreme drinkability.
Our belgian farmhouse ale is rich yet finishes dry with hints of white pepper and fresh squeezed orange juice.
Hazy IPA bursting with tropical flavors enhanced by Phantasm. We were lucky to be one of the few that could get a hold of this Thiol boosting powder!
Fresh Hopped pilsner with fresh hops grown at Talking Farm in Skokie, IL.

Grow Greater IPA, our collaboration with Grow Greater Englewood is available for onsite pick-up and will see distribution for the month of October. This beer is a cool one, Warrior, Idaho 7, Mosaic and the experimental curve of HBC 630 all twist up for a ripe raspberry, fleshy cantaloupe, and raw hop straight from the field mix. Real vibrant for an ABV of 6.3% with aroma streaming from the can.  

Grow Greater Englewood is a nonprofit social enterprise that works with residents and developers in the Englewood neighborhood of Chicago to create sustainable food economies and green businesses to support community wellness and generate wealth. Now and for the future.

A portion of the proceeds from the can sales benefit Grow Greater’s network of black and brown farmers, their project of the Englewood Nature Trail, and supporting the Englewood Village Market. Learn more about their projects at www.growgreater.org.

In-house release - 9/30/21

Distribution release - 10/4/21
Orange Vanilla Sunlight Cream Ale combines smooth malt character with the flavors of vanilla and orange, all with a crisp, clean finish.
GFJ is an American IPA crafted with a unique blend of hops to provide the tropical aromas and flavors of grapefruit, passionfruit, tangerine, and apricot.

A delight for the senses, this beer delivers on all levels. Rosy floral aromas are immediate as you pour, with a light and limey citrus bite on the palate and a balanced but obvious bitterness to finish. Store and enjoy chilled.

Forget the notion this is a style that has had it's day. Instead,think of it as honeycomb covered in chocolate, because that's exactly what it tastes like:rich, unctuous and an absolutely decadent treat.

Mysticism and mayhem lie in the cards. In the cards, you'll see your inner self, hear your inner voice, and debate your inner intuition. This Hazy American Pale Ale is Double Dry Hopped with Citra, Cryo Loral, and Mosaic hops and fermented with Kveik yeast. While we cannot control how your cards fall, we can make the unpredictable present more enjoyable.

Anger and hostility complexes await you, dear beer lover, for this Russian Imperial Stout was not meant for you. Meant only for those that live a life of separation and those that sit in the dark by choice, this deep, mysterious, black as death beer will haunt you at night, leave you weeping in your sleep, and remind you that manners mean nothing to a corpse. Like traveling through the bonfires of Hell, each sip serves as a reminder that you do not belong. You, dear beer lover, are not worthy.

Alluringly tart and fruity, this sour wheat beer is loaded with Blueberry enhancing it’s already magnetic seductiveness. Enchantingly light in body and effervescent, we sour this German-style Berliner Weisse with lactobacillus in the kettle before adding mounds of our favorite blue fruit. Refreshing and easy drinking, this beer is perfect for any time of the year.
An easy drinking Dark Lager, perfect for those colder months. Hints of nut, caramel, toffee, and chocolate lend way to a smooth light finish.

This Double Dry Hopped IPA is a delicious juice bomb thanks to a hefty hopping of Citra, Motueka, & Simcoe hops. An endless succession of juicy pineapple, grapefruit, and tangerine notes are leveled out with a hint of bitterness that resolves onto a smooth and refreshing finish.

Sausage Series. 

Hiya! Chicago style means enjoying a cold beer on your porch. A Superdawg with everything including hot peppers, and absolutely no ketchup, this beer was created to complement the unique flavors of the Windy City's favorite food. Lake Effect Brewing and Superdawg Drive-In, a Chicago style collaboration.

Our dark Bavarian Hefeweizen brewed with blood orange. Bready wheat malt flavors and light hints of chocolate. The traditional banana and clove profile of this style is accented by a fresh citrus character of blood oranges.
A German style Pale Bock. Bready malt characters are balanced by Michigan grown Zuper Sazzer hops for a crisp, yet malty amber lager.
This damn Wee Heavy is so good it will make a saint out of a sinner! Earthy malt greatness with a hint of smoky oak and peat. Balanced and smooth, but watch your back!
Well, as you can imagine, it tastes EXACTLY like a Watermelon Jolly Rancher.  Tasty and crushable!

Imperial Porter brewed with Cocoa Nibs, Hazelnut, Peanut Butter, and Banana.  Long Day?  Cozy up with Fuzzy Socks!  Kick back with these comfy layers of flavor and the smooth silky body of the base beer.  Everyone loves a good pair of fuzzy socks and this beer is our tribute to the comfiest of footwear.
Slow Pour, Traditional German Pilsner
Yorkshire Best Bitter on both regular draft & hand pulled cask.
The annual Oktoberfest beer that Rock Bottom individually brews at each and every one of their restaurants.

beer.beer_name: BEER DOWN IPA - East Coast IPA
beer.beer_description: It's 4th and goal from the third yard line, the clock is ticking down.  It's time to reach for a BEER DOWN IPA!  This East Coast IPA has everything that you want in an IPA and in a beer on game day.  Hopped with Citra, Mosaic and Motueka it packs quite the tropical punch for aromas and flavors.  This completely crushable IPA is perfect for game day, tailgating, sitting round the fire and more.

The dark one rises again, CRYPT KEEPER is back!  Our Imperial Pumpkin Porter is a dark and mysterious concoction that is filled with dark rich chocolate, coffee notes, with pumpkin and spice flavors.  This year we added a touch of milk sugar to add a smoother, creamier mouthfeel.  The decadence and depth of the beer slowly reveals itself as the beer warms; the pumpkin and spice melt through the richness of the chocolate to show the many layers that CRYPT KEEPER has.  One sip and CRYPT KEEPER will grab hold, and never let go.

It’s the dawn of an all-new session IPA! Brewed with an array of malts to provide a deep crimson hue, Scarlet Dawn Session Red IPA employs a range of hops that lend a floral aroma and keep the bitterness to a minimum. It’s straightforward, sessionable and will treat you right – morning, noon or night.
Oat Cream IPA with Citra, Mosaic and Milk Sugar
Ale brewed with Key Lime, Vanilla, and Milk Sugar
Triple New England Style IPA, Triple Dry Hopped with Citra, El Dorado and Mosaic
Three kinds of flavorful hops and hibiscus flowers give this IPA a citrusy intensity. Bold with a pleasantly bitter finish.
Imperial Stout with Coconut and Vanilla

beer.beer_name: Barrel Aged Bananas Foster Imperial Stout (2021)
beer.beer_description: Barrel Aged Imperial Stout with Cinnamon, Maple, Vanilla & Banana
Barrel Aged Wild Ale with Orange Blossom Honey, Green Apples, Figs, and Cardamom

Coming into this world shot from a cannon full of Superbad, SoulMan was born from the lavish half of an experimental partigyle brew. In the same way that the words aren't nearly as important as how you sing them, hand-made salted caramel adds the boogie and the sexual healing to our take on the classic Brown Ale.

Deeply caramelized sugar provides roasted notes that blend in nicely with a rich malty base. Paired with a mild, underlying hop character for a long, dry finish.

A non-alcoholic, full-flavored IPA, dry-hopped with Mosaic & Citra hops. This confounding creation uses the same ingredients found in our highly-balanced IPAs (hops, malt, yeast & water), and thus the same deliciousness, but brewed without the ceremonial fez & ancient incantations that normally take it over the edge.
Note To Self: a hazy IPA brewed with Kohatu, Wai iti , and Mosaic hops. Fermented with a new yeast from Omega called Cosmic Punch. Expect notes of tropical fruits, peach, and apricot.
Tangerine ? IPA

Greetings from Paradise! It’s great here and we’re never leaving! POSTCARDS FROM PARADISE pours a beautiful golden sunset with heavy notes of grapefruit, mango, oak, and coconut. This new West Coast-Style IPA was dry hopped at over 5lbs per barrel with Talus, Citra, and Mosaic. Talus is an insane new hop and we’re loving everything about it.
Fresh strawberries are added between fermentation and carbonation.

A perfect seasonal to celebrate the harvest. This clean, toasty easy drinking brew hits the spot, cheers!
Hops: Crystal, Magnum, & Saaz
This delicious Hazy IPA is packed full of tropical, pineapple and citrus notes.

A double dry hopped hazy IPA that will take you right to a tropical paradise. 

Packed full of notes of pineapple, coconut, and lime (think pina colada).

Contains lactose.

St. Basil the Great was known for his care of the poor and underprivileged. 

As an ode to St. Basil our amber ale is loaded with nearly 4lbs of fresh sweet basil.

Inspired by that last drink of cereal milk, this decadent White Stout, brewed with Saigon cinnamon, Tahitian vanilla bean, and milk sugar, is sure to take you back to simpler times when Saturday morning cartoons were the most important part of the week.
Brewed with several German malts for a malt-driven body with sweet notes of caramel and toffee balanced by a subtle Hallertau Mittelfrüh hopping for a clean, crisp finish.

A crisp and refreshing fruit ale with hints of passionfruit and pineapple. This beer is tropical, aromatic, but not overly sweet. SPF is graced with quenching notes of bright citrus, delicate acidity, and familiar tropical aromas of guava, pineapple, and mango.
Refreshing sweet superfruit citrus with the slightly sweet and subtle spiciness of pure ginger.

Our flagship brand, Miller Lite, is the great tasting, less filling beer that defined the American light beer category in 1975. We deliver a clear, simple message to consumers: \Miller Lite is the better beer choice.\" What's our proof? 
1) Miller Lite is the original light beer. 
2) Miller Lite has real beer taste because it's never watered down. 
3) Miller Lite is the only beer to win four gold awards in the World Beer Cup for best American-style light lager. (2006)

This bruiser of a beer clocks in at 8.0% and is radiant red in color. It comes out swinging with one fist tattooed with hops and the other with malt. First crack at this beer fills you nostrils with sweet sticky hops and a second hit comes with caramel, toffee and flan. That opening sip fills you mouth with dank earthy hops, pine sap and toffee. However, you soon realize that Brass Jar is nothing to be afraid of, it finishes dry and leaves a bit of lingering toffee and hop bitterness. Before you know it, this scary drinkable beer is reduced to a small bit of foam at the bottom of your glass.
Goes well with sizzling meat on a plate, fajitas, roasted potatoes, “We are the Champions” -Queen, rock climbing and redwoods.

Just like your best friend, Trustworthy IPA is something you can always count on. This IPA is generously hopped with Simcoe and Mosaic and has a pale straw color. The initial aroma is a blast of tropical fruit, tangerines and a touch of orange blossom honey. You notice the wonderful white lacing and flavors of green mango, tangerine, resinous hops, orange blossom honey and subtle cracker notes. Before you know it, you’re half way through your pint of Trustworthy IPA. The light malt body helps to really make the hops shine. The firm bitterness lets you know your drinking an IPA but it doesn’t distract you from finishing your pint and wanting another one.
Goes great with a burger and fries, Thai food, pasta, burritos, a good book, Friday nights and those awkward family parties.

Gigil is a our take on the pilsner style and uses 20% Puffed Jasmine Rice as part of the grist. If that sounds like a lot of rice, you're right! It is! The beer is crystal clear, light straw in color and has a tight white foam. Aromas of saltine crackers, subtle tropical fruit from the rice and that crisp lager character invite you to your first sip. The beer is light on your palate and there is a high level of carbonation. Light malt flavors, balanced hop bitterness and refreshing lager character make this beer very enjoyable and very familiar.
Goes well with sushi, pad thai, pho, shishito peppers, Omakase and fun times with friends

The weather is beautiful and I wish you were here! Take a seat, put up your feet, relax, and soak in the moment. Aromas of lemon zest, Noble hops, and flavors of cracker, honey, and a crisp bitterness. You'll be wearing a t-shirt all year long!

The best part of a campfire is completely roasting a marshmallow on the end of a coat hanger. That burnt marshmallow is not only just a tasty treat but that flaming ball of puffed sugar is quite the show. Your first impression of What Plane? is well done marshmallow, graham cracker and baking chocolate. You observe it’s intensely dark color and wonder what else this beer is hiding? A U2 spy plane perhaps? When you hold it to the light, the only thing you see is the tan lacing around your glass, ruby red highlights and beer as black most stealth aircraft. The flavors of the beer aren’t far from the aromas, dark sugar, crispy oatmeal cookies, baking chocolate and espresso.
Goes well with well done smores... duh. BBQ pulled pork or brisket, creamy blue cheese, wild game chili, St. Patty’s Day, campfires, spiking your coffee at work.

One of our most popular beers. This light wheat ale starts out with hints of bright citrus and ends with a creamy vanilla finish. Served tall with a fresh orange slice, Orange Blossom is the perfect relief from the Arizona heat.

An American style Barley Wine,  showcases one of the best dual purpose hops...Cashmere...Molasses, stone fruit and dark raisins leads you into tastes of biscuit and toffee. The 120 minute boil creates the absolute perfect amount of Caramelization which encapsulates the entire experience, both the mouth feel and color.

beer.beer_name: Vanilla Oak Barrel Aged On Chocolate / Black Cherry
beer.beer_description: A crisp, clean and refreshing Cream Ale that was aged in whiskey barrels. Then we added a wonderful HEXX 47% Milk Chocolate and 70% Dark Chocolate and threw in a few black Cherries

This Stout takes all the best qualities from every stout ever made.  It puts all these qualities in one glass (yours).  Once you partake in your first sip...the beautiful dark chocolate and light roasted will be front and center.  Then the complexity of the grain bill will come thru and completely balance the chocolate and roast, leaving you wanting more.

In Collaboration with the HEXX Chocolate Company, we have been able to create something very special.  A crisp, clean and refreshing Cream Ale that smells of wonderful HEXX  47% Milk Chocolate sourced from the village of Mbingu, Near Ifakara, Tanzania.  Then, your sense of taste is melted with an amazing  70% Dark Chocolate, from the same Tanzania Cacoa Bean.
Not your normal cream ale,  vanilla and the perfect amount of oak character will quench your thirst.

All atmospheric nuclear explosions produce a unique and easy to detect emission signature, consisting of an extremely brief and intense initial "flash" followed by a 2nd much longer and less intense "flash" of light (the visible fireball). These dual explosions of light are known as "double flashes". This phenomenon is unique to nuclear explosions and impossible to recreate artificially, allowing researchers, scientists, tracking satellites, and governments to confirm if and where a nuclear explosion has taken place. While not emitting light, our "Double Flash" Dubbel does explode into a deep amber color and tasteful fireball of classic Belgian flavors. The term Dubbel is a Trappist beer naming convention originally used to identify beers with a higher alcohol content. We match that required "emission signature" here as we produce this 7% ABV, classically style Trappist ale. We use a unique combination of Victory, Munich, Belgian Aromatic, and a touch of Dark Crystal malt to create a complex but dry malt character. The Belgian yeast strain produces fruity esters that give you a "Double Flash" of flavor, evoking notes of plum and spice. This brew is easy to track, no satellites necessary, just flash down to our taproom for a pour.

The Vela Incident was an unidentifiable double-flash of light detected in the Indian Ocean on September, 22nd 1979. The double-flash was detected by a Vela Satellite, an American spy satellite specially equipped with sensors designed to detect potential "hidden" nuclear explosions.  On Sept. 22nd, the satellite detected the signature "double-flash" of an atmospheric nuclear explosion with a magnitude of 2 to 3 kilotons. However, other scientific data was inconclusive and there was some debate over the definitive cause of the flash. Speculation has been that the flash was caused by a secretive nuclear test carried out jointly by Israel and South Africa. Amazingly, South Africa had up to 7 assembled nuclear weapons and Israel had been stockpiling neutron bombs. This secretive joint test, known as "Operation Phoenix", was carried out while, supposedly, no Vela satellites were observing the area and IN THE MIDDLE OF A TYPHOON. Well, we have no need to hide our "test" from anything or anyone so we welcome you to "light upon" our newest creation, a Belgian Quadrupel. At 11% ABV this beer is dangerously potent and you'll detect a hidden "double-flash" of flavor as you savor subtle notes of fig and light black pepper. Strong and spicy, with dark fruit notes and some sweetness, but a dry finish....this beer is a tasteful mystery.

Vertical smoke trails, technically known as "atomic smoke trails", are the thin rails of smoke often seen extending upward alongside the mushroom cloud formed by an atomic test. Just prior to detonating an atomic test, rockets were fired from specific locations to leave smoke trails near the explosion and create a visual "grid" of smoke that could be used to register the strength and movement of shock waves created by the blast. Here, we go "off the grid" and craft an eccentric brew, influenced by the Scottish ale style, with hints of Cherrywood and Mesquite smoked malts that help lend complexity and flavor to this slightly fruity, rich, malt-forward ale. We completed our brewing "trail" by aging this beer in Smoke Wagon bourbon barrels which impart a noticeable bourbon barrel character, notes of vanilla and oak, and assist the beer in pouring a beautiful, dark mahogany color.

Honey Dip is an Imperial Stout brewed with honey and Madagascar vanilla beans then aged on American oak. This process creates a well-balanced beer that combines elements of dark malts, vanilla sweetness, and dryness from the oak, to create a velvety smoothness uncommon in this style of beer.

beer.beer_name: Loverboy White Tea Peach Sparkling Hard Tea
beer.beer_description: Sparkling hard tea flavored white tea peach with hints of lavender

Broken Bridge Stout. This is delicious bourbon barrel aged stout collab with our neighbors that is simply beer and barrel (a little lactose) - simple yet good, or better, than most well known brands without the lines.

beer.beer_name: Milk of the Murder Hornet - Piña Colada
beer.beer_description: Milkshake IIPA with Lactose Coconut and Pineapple - 8.5% ABV

A superior light beer. Brewed using the finest barley malt, select grains, all-imported hops and a pure-cultured yeast strain. The special choice of grains combined with the extended mashing process produces a smooth, refreshing beer with fewer carbohydrates.

In this epic battle, the Blood of the Unicorn has been shed by the sword of the deadly assassin of the east. One sip of this aggressively hopped red ale clearly reveals what drives these, the greatest of, hop heads of lore. Is this the end of the mythical horned horse? Or will he rise like the phoenix to fight another day?

Dominant impressions of latte coffee with powerful chocolate aromas in the nose. The alcohol esters are enveloped with hints of autumn wood, citrus zest (orange, lemon) and freshly baked biscuits. The initial taste is sweetly sinful. Beer and chocolate trapped into one single glass, a liquid milky draught with a backbone of bitter malt. The alcohol warms the throat and, in the finish, you will pick up traces of cloves, citrus, orange and mocha.
The heaviest of the Rochefort beers, the 10 is a quadrupel style beer and can be recognized by its blue label.

The unbeatable Pumking recipe was adapted for the stout beer style in 2011. Dark and mysterious, reignite your senses with Warlock's huge roasted malt character, moderate carbonation and a spiced pumpkin aroma.

beer.beer_name: Harvest Ale (Matured In Lagavulin Whisky Casks)

beer.beer_description: Open Tab is a Scottish-style 80 Shilling brewed with British malt and hops. Malty, rich and full-bodied, yet remarkably sessionable and clean. Having just the one? Keep it open.

A shandy is beer mixed with a little something extra like soda, juice or ginger ale. Leinenkugel’s® Summer Shandy® is a traditional wheat beer with refreshing natural lemonade flavor that makes it perfect for the sun-splashed summer months. For a fun and fresh food pairing, try it with lighter, brighter foods like shrimp quesadillas, pan-seared scallops with lemon vinaigrette, or lemon chicken with pasta.

Miodowy Ciemny Lager / Honey Dark Lager, 14.8°Blg

Piwo Na Miodzie Gryczanym – wysoka jakość i niepowtarzalność tego trunku potwierdzona jest między innymi nagrodą Grand Prix na prestiżowym konkursie piwnym Chmielaki Krasnostawskie w 2011 roku.
"Najlepsze z najlepszych"- piwo warzone z dodatkiem jakże niedocenianej gryki, należycie odleżakowane i tuż przed rozlewem dosładzane doskonałym miodem gryczanym. Brak etapu filtracji pozwala zachować w pełni prozdrowotne właściwości piwa wynikające między innymi z zawartości drożdży browarniczych i miodu.
Nagrody: Grand Prix (Ogólnopolskie Święto Chmielarzy i Piwowarów 2011), I miejsce w kategorii piwo smakowe (Konsumencki Konkurs Piw Chmielaki Krasnostawskie 2011), I miejsce w kategorii piw na miodzie (Konsumencki Konkurs Piw Bractwa Piwnego 2012), II miejsce w kategorii piwa aromatyzowane (Plebiscyt Na Piwo Roku Browar.biz 2012), godło "Teraz Polska" (XXIII Edycja Konkursu Na Najlepsze Produkty i Usługi 2013).
Najlepsze do lodów i deserów.

An oasis of flavor in the desert of normalcy, this cocktail-inspired imperial gose is brewed with agave and sea salt then aged in tequila barrels. When it emerges we hit it with a healthy dose of prickly pear extract, lending the liquid its flamboyant fuchsia glow and mellowing out the tangy tartness with hints of berry and melon. It’s no mirage, it’s the real deal. ¡Más Agave Clásica Prickly Pear!

We’ve gone through great lengths to refine the process to yield a Rich and Creamy Flavor and mouth feel to show case the decadent flavors yet leave the harsh taste that dark grains can often leave behind. Incredible mouthfeel yet not cloyingly sweet to aid in its drinkability.
Imagine a smooth, clean wheat beer with a touch of peach and you get the idea behind O'Fallon Wheach, our peach wheat beer. Light, refreshing and crisp, it's perfect for any occasion!

Żywiec Porter, pronounced "je-vi-ets", is a dark, strong beer brewed according to the traditional recipe from 1881, with the Munich malt and special malts for caramel and color plus the highest quality aromatic hops. Everything together creates a unique combination of taste. Production of this Porter was moved to Bracki Bowar in 2004.

21°Blg
Barleywine aged in 2nd-use bourbon barrels

BREWED WITH MOLASSES. TOUCHES OF COCONUT AND 
VANILLA.

Aged in the third-use barrels that were once home to Kentucky bourbon and then our renowned Bourbon County Stout, this traditional English-style barleywine possesses the subtlety of flavor that only comes from a barrel that’s gone through many seasons of ritual care. The intricacies of the previous barrel denizens – oak, charcoal, hints of tobacco and vanilla, and that signature bourbon heat – are all present in this beer. Hearty and complex, Bourbon County Brand Barleywine is a titan and a timeline; a bold, flavorful journey through the craft of barrel aging.

Collusion collaboration series.

Maibock-style pale "pseudo-lager" brewed with specialty Lutra yeast. This ale, designed and brewed in collaboration with Switchyard Brewing Company, is a "smooth, malty ale with the body of a lager. Oh, the humanity!"
pie inspired sour ale rested on raspberries, blueberries, vanilla wafers, vanilla and milk sugar

Boskeun is the nickname of Jo, one of the two brothers who preferred to brew blond beer at home. It is a special Easter beer, one of the first real Belgian Easter beers. (Slaghmuylder's paasbier being first). It has been brewed with pale malt, Golding hops, cane sugar and refermented in the bottle. It's a seasonal beer, so we suggest not to keep it eternally. The name Boskeun means rabbit of the wood (virgin wood, maybe?) and the label shows it, sampling the last brew.

This brawny, tawny ale is a savory celebration of spicy rye malt and rye whiskey, compliments of extended aging in freshly-emptied Templeton Rye barrels. Rye on Rye pours a deep amber and evokes notes of charred oak and vanilla, with a finish that is delightfully boozy and sweet!
