Kentucky ale brewed with  strawberries and aged in first use bourbon barrels for at least 6 weeks.

Kentucky Vanillla Barrel Cream Ale is our take on a classic American style of beer. We took a cold-conditioned cream ale brewed with a hint of flaked corn and bourbon vanilla beans and aged it in freshly decanted Kentucky bourbon barrels for a minimum of two months. A perfect blend of vanilla and bourbon notes make this cream ale irresistible. The medium body and 5.5% ABV make Kentucky Vanilla Barrel Cream Ale the perfect complement to any dessert, or all day event.
Imperial Stout with tons of roasted dark malts, give way to hints of coffee and chocolate balanced with big hop additions.

Named Cinq Cents in 75 cl (25.4 fl.oz.) bottles, this beer, with its typical golden color, slightly hazy appearance and fine head, is especially characterized by its aroma which results from an agreeable combination of fresh hops and yeast.

It was first brewed by the monks of Chimay at Scourmont Abbey in 1966.

Above all it is the fruity notes of muscat and raisins that give this beer a particularly attractive aroma.

beer.beer_name: Chico’s Revenge Imperial Oatmeal Milk Stout
beer.beer_description: Big milk stout brewed w/oats, lactose, and love. Big sweet chocolate notes.

beer.beer_name: Me Love To Eat Cream Filled Cookies
beer.beer_description: Imperial stout with chocolate, cream filled chocolate cookies, vanilla beans and lactose.
Imperial start with chocolate, graham crackers, marshmallows, and vanilla.

The allusion to pink elephants and the choice of names is not due to chance. With a particular character, the unique taste results from triple fermentation and the use of three different yeast strains. Sweet, biscuit malt backbone, supported by pleasant warmth and spice, finishes well rounded, floral, and dry.

Our golden-yellow wheat beer, with its fine-pored white foam, smells of cloves and impresses consumers with its refreshing banana flavour. It is full bodied and with a smooth yeast taste. To be enjoyed at any time (always a pleasure / enjoyment), goes excellently with fish and seafood, with spicy cheese and especially with the traditional Bavarian veal sausage. Brewed according to our centuries-old brewing tradition on the Weihenstephan hill.
Floor Malted Bohemian Pilsner Malts with Zuper Saaz hops.

A beer so enticing you may think it's nectar from the gods. The name "Hala Kahiki"(hahlah-kah-hee-kee), originates from the Hawaiian words for pineapple. Feel the way it rolls off your tongue? Our sweet and refreshing beer will take you away ...have a sip ...grab a lei!

beer.beer_name: Might Meets Right (Peppermint Hot Cocoa Barrel Aged) (2020)
beer.beer_description: Peppermint & chocolate! (Plus marshmallow & vanilla!) This one is definitely a keeper, but you'll likely not want to wait to drink it. We only made two kegs of it last year, but people kept asking for it, so here it is, canned and ready to go!

beer.beer_name: Might Meets Right (¡La Sorpresa! Barrel Aged) (2020)
beer.beer_description: Our riff on a Mexican hot chocolate with roasted cacao nibs, espresso powder, vanilla, toasted cinnamon, and ancho, New Mexico, and arbol chiles. A rich & complex beer with a picante finish!

beer.beer_name: Lake Superior Bourbon Barrel Aged Barleywine

beer.beer_description: Imperial Stout with chocolate, pecan, and toasted coconut.

beer.beer_name: Hala Kahiki Aged In Rhine Hall Pineapple Brandy Barrels 2021

beer.beer_description: Yes, Strawberry Jacket. A slightly drier blend of bourbon and rye whiskey barrel English Barleywines aged eighteen months provides a base for the delicate nuances of fresh strawberry to shine while retaining the same balance we expect of our beloved Straight Jacket. Reminiscent a fresh, juicy strawberry atop a crème brûlée, this sipper can accompany dessert or stand on its own. Enjoy now or store cold.

Inspired in part by the disconcertingly large gravitational singularity at the center of our galaxy, we devised Supermassive Café Deth to be the midpoint of a theoretical bourbon barrel-aged stout-coffee continuum. After a painstaking eighteen months of aging, this slightly sweet blend of Deth's Tar meets its cosmic binary in the form of freshly roasted Dark Matter coffee to the tune of ten pounds per oak barrel. Enjoy immediately or store cold.

A celebration of malt, oak, and patience, Very Special Old [Straight] Jacket is a cuvée of English Barleywines each aged between two and four years in our favorite bourbon barrels. Lusciously sweet and colossally complex, V.S.O.J. is equal parts refinement and excess.

Trust the Gold Standard, our abbey-style blonde ale. With a golden body befitting of its name, this ale pairs dynamic, fruity and spicy Belgian esters with malty flavors of honey and biscuit. Tangy blood orange and a unique, blush hue makes this special summer release worth its weight.

Tequila Barrel Sunrise is a spirited riff on the classic namesake cocktail, aged in Extra Añejo tequila barrels and infused with orange zest and hibiscus. The result is a uniquely delicious Blonde Barleywine that offers an authentic Tequila Sunrise sipping experience.
Amber colored and medium-bodied Belgian strong ale with notes of candied fruits and spices, malty caramel, and warming alcohol.
Luscious chocolate meets rich roasted malts in this sweet stout.

KBS gets its coffee fix in the very first variant to come from our beloved bourbon barrel-aged stout.  Yes, KBS may already be brewed with coffee, but it gets some extra oomph when it’s aged on espresso beans after being removed from barrels.  The result is a fresh and snappy coffee twist on our classic barrel-aged beer.  Who says you can’t start your day with a barrel-aged stout?

Claim a special Exemption, our abbey-style tripel, with its smooth, malty body matched with an intensely flavorful trifecta of raspberries, ginger and citrus. Bright and tart berry notes alongside zesty lemon peel, coriander and ginger will leave your taste buds tingling.

No sparging, sprinkling, diluting or extra water here. We loaded our mash tun to the brim with 1.5 tons of delicious Belgian malt, mashed it once and took only the first (and best) runnings. Sure, it might be downright inefficient, but it also creates a uniquely smooth, rich and robust malty body to complement the intense, tropical flavors of our farmhouse yeast. Procure this ale while you can, before our accountants found out what we did.

2021 is all about you, taurus. get ready for electric energy and good luck all month, beginning with a sweet pick-me-up from this tiramisu imperial stout.
the early days of may bring drama from a certain venus in your life, but don't worry. mercury ascends just when you need it, creating a buzz of positive communication and unexpected romance. and because spring is the season of renewal, expect a fresh flow of energy all taurus season starting with the bold flavors of coffee, vanilla, chocolate, and milk sugar in this new ferndale project favorite.
Honey ale

beer.beer_name: Hazelnut Pot De Crème (All Canned Dates)
beer.beer_description: Imperial Stout with chocolate, hazelnut, vanilla beans & lactose
Imperial stout aged on vanilla beans

beer.beer_name: Milk of the Murder Hornet - Pineapple
beer.beer_description: Pineapple IIPA with Lactose, Vanilla Beans, and Pineapple

beer.beer_name: Guava & Passionfruit Milk of the Murder Hornet
beer.beer_description: Milkshake IIPA brewed with Mosaic hops, lactose, vanilla, guava, and passion fruit, and it tastes even better than it sounds. Our latest extension of this series is just in time for warm weather and our hornets are buzzing with excitement.

Our Pommeau is made from locally grown bittersweet cider apples which are hand-harvested and 'sweated' at cool temperatures. After the apples have sweetened, the fresh-pressed juice is fermented and aged with apple eau de vie. Our Pommeau is then matured in French oak barrels for one year. The result is a tremendously complex apple Pommeau that blossoms with aromas of fresh-pressed cider, dried fruit, and wood. This bottle will improve with cellaring for up to 20 years.
Brewed in the Russian Imperial Stout style, this offering boasts plenty of malt character and an aggressive amount of hops. A rich, flavorful ale with a finish you won’t believe.

beer.beer_name: Origin of Darkness w/ Maple Syrup & Walnuts
beer.beer_description: These barrels have been through the ringer! They started with bourbon, moved on to maple syrup, and finally they’re finishing off with our delicious Imperial Stout base, brewed in collaboration with the Chicago-based brewery Mikerphone. All those layers are the perfect blend of Americana and Canadiana, finished with an additional dose of that sweet syrup we all love, and toasted walnuts for a classic pairing.
An English-style brown ale with a malt profile of caramel, toffee and cocoa. A dark ale that is well rounded with a malty sweet flavor with clean finish.

You can't always get what you want..... but sometimes you get lucky. It's all about the right hops, at the right time. This is how Melvin Grew Up. Fruity, Intense, but not bitter like the rest of them. As long as you don't take advantage, we think this is the hoppiest relationship you could ask for. ABV 7.5%
Named for Pako (say “PACO”) the dog (No wait, Pako’s not a dog!) This full flavored, fully hop-evident IPA will have the hopheads rejoicing. Explosive hop aroma from a pungent Simcoe/columbus blend.

We start with our traditional Cream Ale recipe, adding huckleberries
during the last minutes of the boil to lend a subtle berry aroma and flavor.

After weeks of lagering, this German Kellerbier is as seasoned and smooth as the expert paddlers of the area.  With a deep golden color and balanced malt backbone, this malt lager finishes as crisp as it starts. River Wizard is the perfect beer for lazy floats on the Madi or for post splash's down the Mad Mile.

This Imperial Rice Lager has bright fruity aromas reminiscent of Runts™️, cracker, and citrus. Light bodied, brightly carbonated, and finishes like a refreshing cold sake. A hint of spicy hot bitterness lingers into the finish.

Just in time for warm summer days, our Witbier is light and effervescent, but packed with refreshing, summery flavor.  Orange peel and coriander give this beer a zesty, fruity aroma without overpowering the palate.  With a strong wheat backbone the beer is rich in texture but the high carbonation makes it bright and will leave you quenched!

This Belgian single will bring out the Trappist monk in all of us. This light bodied sipper has notes of banana and German noble hops. With a crisp finish, Small Axe is the perfect beer for you recreation day or to sip while you're working around the house...or the monastery!

This fruited ale is brewed with 100% Montana grain and has a silky smooth mouthfeel with a medium to full body. Dank hop character, juicy fruit, and vanilla round out the aroma. A slight hop bitterness paired with a tart strawberry creates a delicious melody of hop and fruit swirls.

Our flagship offering is golden to pale in color,
with low bitterness, medium body, and a white
head. Our Cream Ale has redefined the category
and made a classic style cool again. We use
a bit of Madagascar Vanilla Bean to give it that
“Cream Soda” kick. This beer finishes dry despite
a subtle perceived sweetness from the Vanilla.
Great any time of year.

beer.beer_name: Gordon Bombay Was In Our Taproom Once
beer.beer_description: Imperial Brown Ale Aged in Bourbon Barrels
25th anniversary ale aged in Bourbon barrels
Buckley aged 12-18 months in BLIS maple syrup bourbon barrles

Belgian Ale fermented in rum barrels with plums.

What makes it even more special is that we added a  Brettanomyces blend to give it some tartness/funk and should help this age over the next couple years.

After tasting through our rackhouse of spirits barrel-aged beers, we selected a complex blend that evolves as you drink. Rackhouse Reserve incorporates ales aged in a variety of bourbon barrels for up to 18 months, culminating in a harmony of warm flavors reminiscent of caramel, toasted marshmallow, spicy oak and dark chocolate.
tart and refreshing with a distinctive chocolate and caramel aroma background.  aged in cabernet barrels for one year.
Tepache-inspired mixed culture saison with pineapple, cinnamon, coriander, long peppercorns, and grains of paradise.
Did someone say cake? This robust porter has been aged in rum barrels and comes together with vanilla and natural flavorings to deliver a cake experience in liquid form.
Barrel aged American Wild Ale with grapefruit, prickly pear, and watermelon.

Wild ale aged in wine barrels with pomegranate, cherry, strawberry and hibiscus. 

We used a brux variant of Brettanomyces yeast and aged a wheat ale in wine barrels for a year with several additions of fruit, sparking secondary fermentation. The resulting beer is a balance of fruit, tartness and barrel character.
A big Barleywine meets the flavors of Scotland. Peaty, smoky, delicious. Aged in Islay Scotch barrels.

Gose Series. 

The Gose Project is about taking the same base beer and aging it in several different barrels to see how the wood and spirit of each barrel influence the base.

«Львівське Портер» — особливий сорт темного пива із солодовим і винним присмаком. Цей хмільний напій має унікальний букет шліфованого століттями аромату. «Львівське Портер» ідеально підходить для компанії давніх друзів, яким є що розповісти одне одному та поділитись спогадами.
Delightful medley of strawberries, apricot, and apple. The fruits of fair weather beckon.
Another DryHop collaboration! Refreshing and well-balanced, this hoppy wheat has the full body of a wheat beer, and the bite of an IPA.

beer.beer_name: Dragon’s Milk Reserve: Double Bourbon Barrel-Aged Stout With Madagascar & Indonesian Vanilla Beans (2021-2)

beer.beer_description: Beer and Kombucha blend, infused w/Hibiscus

Cool off this Summer with a juicy and refreshing Chicago favorite built for the season. Bask in radiant citrus notes while soaking up its floral ambiance. By the time the leaves change, our Summer Ale will be just a sun-dappled memory, so crush a few while you've got the chance.

Rye Ale aged in rye barrels. 

Bourbon and rye barrels work together in harmony to breathe life into our Ryewine. This unforgettable ale is brewed with over 60% rye, yielding entirely unique malt- and barrel-derived complexities. Enjoy an ample body that suggests sweetness but still finishes smooth and dry. Enjoy life now, or store cold.

After 18 months in rye whiskey barrels and an addition of unfermented berries, this special dry blend of Ryewine emerges with a wondrous array of oak-derived flavors and balance. Cherry, vanilla, and spice from the barrel meet restrained maple, caramel, and aged malt complexities.  Blackberry, raspberry, boysenberry, and cranberry shine through the end result with perfect balance.
Juicy watermelon and cool mint beat the heat in this fresh submission to the Freedom Series of Session Sours made with real fruit.

This is a raw, unboiled ale was brewed with blackberries, peaches, milk sugar, vanilla & hibiscus and dry-hopped with mosaic. Fermented with Kveik yeast and active lactobacillus plantarum, it’s tart, fruity, and delightfully weird. Cheers!

Staropolskie Miodne to piwo o wyjątkowym smaku, warzone z użyciem podwójnej dawki naturalnego miodu pszczelego. Połączenie wiedzy staropolskich piwowarów i miodosytników.

Piwo miodowe, jasne, pasteryzowane. Składniki: woda, słody: pilzneński; chmiele: Magnum, Hallertauer Tradition; naturalny miód (60g/litr), drożdże dolnej fermentacji. 10°Blg

D0 2017 roku jako Staropolskie Podwójnie Miodowe.
All Citra hopped APA

Bell's Oberon is a wheat ale fermented with Bell's signature house ale yeast, mixing a spicy hop character with mildly fruity aromas. The addition of wheat malt lends a smooth mouthfeel, making it a classic summer beer.
Fragrant, robust, and full bodied, this classic Trappist Quadrupel is mahogany in color and crowned with a dense, tan, frothy head. Its multi-forward flavor profile yields to a warm finish.

If you’ve ever had the pleasure of enjoying a slice of the real-deal Baden-Württemberg torte, if you closed your eyes you’d think you’re drinking a slice. Upon first sip, you’re treated to the sweet tang of sour cherries and ride the flavor wave down to the dark chocolate depths. How did we achieve such perfection? By brewing with cocoa nibs, vanilla beans and two types of cherries.
Nordic honey wine with ginger and hops added.

Duvel is a natural beer with a subtle bitterness, a refined flavour and a distinctive hop character. The unique brewing process, which takes about 90 days, guarantees a pure character, delicate effervescence and a pleasant sweet taste of alcohol.

Apart from pure spring water, which is the main ingredient of beer, barley is the most important raw material. Barley must germinate for five days in the malt house, after which malt remains. The colour of the malt and as a consequence also of the beer is determined by the temperature. Duvel obtains its typical bitterness by adding various varieties of aromatic Slovenian and Czech hops. We use only exclusive hops that are renowned for their constant, outstanding quality.

Duvel ferments for the first time in tanks at 20 to 26°C. The brewer uses his own culture for this. The original yeast strain, which Victor Moortgat himself selected in the 1920’s, originates from Scotland. After maturing in storage tanks in which the beer is cooled down to -2°C, the drink is ready for bottling. Thanks to the addition of extra sugars and yeast, the beer ferments again in the bottle. This occurs in warm cellars (24°C) and takes two weeks. Then the beer is moved to cold cellars, where it continues to mature and stabilise for a further six weeks. This extra long maturation period is unique and contributes to the refined flavour and pure taste of Duvel.

Our Free Wave Hazy IPA is meant for the open road. Whether you’re cruising the Pacific Coast Highway in a convertible or tracing your way up the coast on your bike, our Free Wave doesn’t cut corners. This mouth watering IPA is loaded with Amarillo, Citra, and Mosaic hops.

Brewed with wheat, oats, and lactose for that thick and creamy body you've come to expect from the Shakey surname. Dry-hopped with Mosaic, Mosaic Cryo and El Dorado hops and hit hard with Vanilla post fermentation. The tropical fruit and citrus notes mingle perfectly with the sweet flavors of vanilla transporting you right back to those ice cream shop dayz.
Neutronium Imperial Rye Stout fermented with Brett. and funked for 1 year.
Imperial Rye Stout aged in Woodford Reserve Double Oak barrels for 12 months. 2020 release.

Big, chewy, sweet Imperial
Milk Stout. Made with organic, single-origin coffee sourced
from Kusanya Cafe in
Englewood, by way of our
friends at
tinyshopgrocer.com.
Squeaky clean, malt-focused lagerbier.
A summery wheat beer with citra, amarillo and grapefruit zest.
Double Barrel Aged American Wild Ale with Limes , Oranges, and Salt  Aged in Wine barrels and tequilla barrels for 16 months total.

beer.beer_name: Bourbon Barrel Aged Peanut Butter S'more (2021)
beer.beer_description: For this batch, we let our Imperial Peanut Butter Cup rest in Buffalo Trace Barrels for 18 months. We then blended it with Chocolate pot de Crème Barrels that were sleeping since 2019.  These barrels gave us flavors of Chocolate, Graham  Cracker and Oak. We blended to taste and added mounds of toasted marshmallow to finish it off. This is such a treat!
Barrel aged imperial stout fermented with cinnamon, maple syrup, vanilla and lactose. Aged 17 months in Buffalo Trace barrels

beer.beer_name: Chocolate & Raspberry Pot De Crème (All Canned Dates)
beer.beer_description: Imperial Stout fermented with chocolate, raspberries and lactose

Honey Lager

Łomża Miodowe was created as a blend of the local beer and natural honey from apiaries located near Łomża. The quality of the honey used in brewing processes gives this particular type of beer the delicate, sweet-bitter taste and slight honey aroma.

He’s the sweetest white bulldog you ever did meet! This beer is dedicated to #BearKennedy, who resides in Raleigh, North Carolina. Enjoy this creamy stout with hints of marshmallow, vanilla, and cloudberry — just like a warm Bear snuggle.
English style Barleywine aged in Route 12 rye whiskey barrels.
BA imperial stout with coconut

beer.beer_name: Black Pit of Hatred Imperial Stout
beer.beer_description: Black pit of hatred is a furious, yawning chasm of roasty despair with wretched notes of dark fruit and fermented with the angriest hornindal Kveik we could find. Consume it before it consumes you.

beer.beer_name: Barrel-Aged Vanilla Black Pit of Hatred
beer.beer_description: Imperial Stout aged in bourbon barrels with vanilla beans.

Brewed with dark roasted coffee, flaked oats, cinnamon, nutmeg, clove, and lactose. This stout is a energetic revelation of spice and flavor in Non Alcoholic craft beer. Part cold brew coffee, part classic stout, the Intrepid Traveler is brewed for open road adventurers to enjoy 24/7.

This is the beer that started it all. Mike’s friends like to challenge him and they asked him to make a German Kölsch. He researched the style and played around with the recipe until he found perfection, at least in his mind. Mike’s Kölsch is German in nature, but is unfiltered and has a caramel color with a slight cloudy character.

beer.beer_name: Plant Based Double IPA With Mango & Palm Sugar
beer.beer_description: Double India pale ale with mango & coconut palm sugar. Hopped with Citra, Sabro & Galaxy. All-natural. 100% vegan. Ⓥ

Treat yourself to a rare delight. The voluminous raspberry bouquet will greet you long before your lips touch your glass. Serve this Wisconsin framboise very cold in a champagne flute. Then hold your glass to a light and enjoy the jewel-like sparkle of a very special ale.

Oregon proudly shares their harvest of mouth watering berries, which we ferment spontaneously in large oak vats. Then we employ Wisconsin farmed wheat and year old Hallertau hops to round out this extravaganza of flavor.
Served in a unique jade green bottle shaped like a laughing Buddha!

Unlock the Vault, our series committed to the careful, prolonged conditioning of barrel-aged ales. For those qualified, try our Qualified quadrupel brewed with maple syrup and aged in maple syrup barrels. Rich notes of dark fruit and caramel are enriched with toffee and oak barrel character. To make this delicious winter warmer, we aged our Qualified quadrupel in maple syrup barrels from Yancey's Sugarbush owned by the family of our head brewer, David Yancey, located in upstate New York. Available now in cans and kegs, Maple Barrel Qualified won't last long!

beer.beer_name: Bourbon Barrel Aged Chocolate Salted Caramel Sleepy Bear
beer.beer_description:
Tasting Notes: Dark Chocolate - Rich Toffee – Old Stock Bourbon

We took one of our favorite variants of our Sleepy Bear series and aged it in a blend of Weller and Buffalo Trace Mash #1 barrels for 12 – 16 months. Loaded with roasted cacao nibs, vanilla, caramel and flaked Maldon sea salt this beer is what Chocolatiers dream about. This is one hell of a rich decadent dessert beer that is meant to be enjoyed in great company.

This is Parabola 2020, a one-of-a-kind imperial stout that never fails to impress. Aged for one year in premium bourbon barrels to gain depth, complexity and intensity, then blended and released in limited quantities. 

Righteously dark and thick, with boldly balanced flavors of chocolate, charred oak, vanilla, black cherry and coffee.

MALTS: Crisp Maris Otter Pale, Munich, Cara-hell, Carafa, Dark & Light Crystal, Chocolate, Oats, Roasted Barley

HOPS: Bittering—Zeus; Late Kettle—Hallertau
Imperial version of "Stormcat", mosaic hopped amber ale.
Sputnik Coffee suit with a hint of caramel

beer.beer_name: Chocolate Pot De Crème (All Canned Dates)
beer.beer_description: Imperial stout brewed with chocolate, vanilla and lactose.

Witness the firepower of this fully operational Barrel-Aged Imperial Oatmeal Stout. Brewed with English specialty malts and the addition of flaked and malted oats to create a rich, chocolaty profile and silky mouthfeel that cloaks its considerable strength. The American oak barrels continue to build layers of complexity, reminiscent of vanilla, toasted coconut and caramel candy after aging this dark menace a full 12 months.
Strong coffee notes with a hint of maple

When the popular English Porter started traveling up the Baltic coast in the 1800s, brewers in Sweden, Finland, Poland, and Russia adapted the style and made it their own. This Dovetail version is based on the Baltic Porters we love to pick up at the Polish delis on the West Side. It's our darkest lager; capped by a large stand of cream-colored foam to showcase deep and rich malt aromas of milk chocolate, raisins, and restrained coffee roast. It's smooth and balanced, but exhibits slightly more bravado and complexity than its English counterparts.

The artist formally known as It Takes Two is now Reprise. 

This West Coast-style IPA clocks packs a punch beyond fragrant hop aroma with its bright citrus, passion fruit, papaya and lime notes.
Brewed and dry-hopped with 2.5 pounds per barrel of Amarillo. Dry in the beginning, with a nice malt middle and a huge hop finish, this big IPA brings notes of bright fruit and citrus.
A limited DDH pale ale hopped with Mosaic and Rakau. Crisp and refreshing with juicy notes of tangerine, mango, and apricot.

Born anew and rising into something greater, we give you PHOENIX TEARS, our Vienna Style Lager. Created using a blend of imported German malts, brewed via a traditional decoction mash, and fermented in our open fermenter with our house lager strain used to ferment our Oktoberfest and Doppelbock biers! It's blazing red hue, rich toasted malt character, light caramel kiss, and dry finish should transport you to lager heaven!

beer.beer_name: Origin of Darkness W/ Almond Milk & Coffee
beer.beer_description: In an homage to their iconic Beer Geek Breakfast series, we brewed a vegan-latte inspired imperial stout. Aged in freshly emptied Kentucky Bourbon Barrels, this brew gets a jolt of caffeine from roasted coffee beans from Detour Coffee, and some smoothness from Almond Milk from Earth’s Own plant based beverage company.

Remember when we went down to Wild Turkey last spring and picked out a house barrel? Well the second that the bourbon was dumped and put into bottles last fall, we drove down to Kentucky to pick it up and brought it straight back to Mousetrap where we put some beer in it while the barrel was still wet. And now it’s ready! So, what is it? (Semi) Well Behaved Turkeys is a wild ale that rested in our Italian Barolo foeder for nine months before being racked directly into our fresh bourbon barrel where it finished for six months. This beer has notes of cola and cherry skin on the nose, tangerine undertones, pleasant acidity and plenty of subtle vanilla notes from the barrel (pardon us, DOUBLE BARREL).

Our tart and slightly savory gose base ale is resting in several different barrels to see how each barrel and previous occupant showcase flavor accents on this rather impressionable base. 

This variety rested in gin barrels for several months and displays brilliant botanical flavors of juniper, coriander, citrus, ginger and oak. It's a lot like a walk in the forest.

This massive Imperial Stout is made with Golden Promise, caramel and chocolate malts, and belgian candi sugar.  We then boiled it for 6 hours and put it in bourbon barrels in which they have rested for over a year.  Dark, rich and smooth flavors of molasses, marshmallow, coconut and dark fruits.
Imperial Milk Stout aged in Basil Haden High Rye (2020) / Breckenridge Rye (2019) Bourbon barrels with Cocoa Nibs, Maple, Vanilla Bean, and Papau New Guinea coffee.

beer.beer_name: Might Meets Right (Heaven Hill Barrel Aged) (2019)
beer.beer_description: Heaven Hill is the stalwart, the pure experience to which the others are compared: rich dark malts collide with vanilla, oak, and a hint of sweet bourbon.
Barrel Aged Barley Wine Style Ale

beer.beer_name: Your Brain On Brunch With Coffee
beer.beer_description: Imperial stout with maple syrup, Dark Matter coffee, fenugreek, vanilla, lactose, and cacao nibs.

beer.beer_name: Imperial Smells Like Bean Spirit - Double Maple
beer.beer_description: Imperial Breakfast Stout w/ Tugboat Sumatra Coffee and Vermont Maple Syrup
Barrel aged American Wild Ale with Hibiscus Flowers and Navel Oranges
Blueberry cider dry-hopped with Mosiac. Just what the doctor ordered.

Like ten pounds of Deth in a five pound bag -- this micro blend of extra-old Deth's Tar sweet component combines intense malt-derived flavors of chocolate, marzipan, and raisin with a wondrously expressive, Samoa cookie-like lumber profile that's just assertive enough to balance its generous sweetness and not dominate the finish.

A weaponized quantity of freshly roasted whole bean coffee from Dark Matter Coffee Roasters imbues our Deth’s Tar Barrel-Aged Imperial Oatmeal Stout with assertive coffee aromatics without overshadowing the base beer on the palate. Pair with rich food or enjoy on its own. Keep cold. Enjoy now. We mean it.

After two years in a pair of Woodford Double Oak barrels we may as well have called this one “Deth by Lumber”. A year ago this beer was sweet, tart, and fruity. Today it feels far more nimble - the oak and fruit competing for your affection with every sip

Our Institutionalized Barleywine takes shelter in Cognac barrels for 12 months before emerging imbued with characteristics of one of the worlds most storied spirits. French oak adds character that is subdued but complex as compared to American varieties, making this a perfect beer for the best of times or the end of times. Enjoy now or store cold.

beer.beer_name: Milk of the Murder Hornet - Mango
beer.beer_description: Milkshake IIPA with lactose, vanilla, & mango.

Made from two row and malted wheat, Bourbon County Brand Wheatwine debuts this year. As the first recipe to veer from the original Imperial Stout since Barleywine in 2013, Wheatwine displays a deep amber color, lighter than its counterparts and acts a true medium to convey the characteristics of our 4+ year old Heaven Hill Bourbon barrels. Wheatwine overflows with flavors of caramel, vanilla, butterscotch, and toffee.

Aged in the second-use barrels that were once home to Kentucky bourbon, this traditional English-style barleywine possesses the subtlety of flavor that only comes from a barrel that’s gone through many seasons of ritual care. The intricacies of the previous barrel denizens – oak, charcoal, hints of tobacco and vanilla, and that signature bourbon heat – are all present in this beer. Hearty and complex, Bourbon County Brand Barleywine is a titan and a timeline; a bold, flavorful journey through the craft of barrel aging.
Our mole-inspired imperial stout w/ almond flour, chocolate, cinnamon, vanilla beans, and ancho, guajillo, and habanero chiles; fermented on toasted oak, then rested on Mexican Chiapas coffee beans.

beer.beer_name: Dragon’s Milk Reserve: Bourbon Barrel-Aged Stout With Peanut Butter & Cocoa Nibs (2021-1)
beer.beer_description: This Reserve is a rich and nutty take on our legendary bourbon barrel-aged stout. Waves of smooth, velvety flavors wash over your taste buds to conjure the familiar taste of peanut butter cups. Aged in select bourbon barrels for three months and finished with massive amounts of real peanut butter and cocoa nibs, our latest Reserve is an indulgent experience that is sure to satisfy your sweet tooth.
Our massive Russian Imperial Stout contains waves of chocolate, coffee, cherry, raisin, and toffee, plus a non-traditional dose of aromatic hops.
Imperial Stout with Maple.
Coconut and vanilla bean imperial stout aged for 12 months in South American Rum Barrels.
Barrel Aged American Wild Ale with Black Currants  & Vanilla Beans

Once a year, we all get to attain a very high status.  Like high, like astronaut high.  The biggest beer we make, it gets pretty crazy with the flavors.  Cherry, coconut, vanilla, cinnamon, roasty coffee, pipe tobacco, chewy malt, and sherry are just a few of the flavor parts of this complex sipper.

beer.beer_name: Milk of the Murder Hornet - Peach
beer.beer_description: Milkshake IIPA with lactose, peach, & vanilla.

John Dough's run-in with Grandma's little darlings didn't quite go as planned. Seems his gingerbread birthday suit and holiday aroma causes kids of all ages to run at him with wide open mouths and screams of glee. We trust this Gingerbread treat will cause you to do the same... his days are numbered!
Attaboy Baldwin! This best friend brings gifts of roasty, chocolatey pleasure with loyalty & heroism. Perfectly balanced to warm your soul and make your tail wag. Lap it up.
Magically packed with citrus piquancy, aromatic pine, and plenty of adventure… so keep your bum on the saddle and enjoy this hop-forward, smooth-drinking ride!

Juicy, sessionable pale ales weren't around when Frances Stupey built his Highland Park log cabin in 1847, yet we're sure Frances would LOVE our DDH sessionable Pale Ale. It's hazy and full of the natural, hand-crafted goodness expected from all good pioneers!
Brewed with Mosaic & Ekuanot hops.
You love food. You love trucks. You love food trucks. We honor these noble carriages with a beer of equal humility and deliciousness. Step up to the window and enjoy!
Who is John Grunsfeld? A hard-working, visionary lad who enjoys his much-deserved, easy-drinking goodness. Free buoyancy with every sip!
A blend of English-style Barleywine and Imperial Stout, conditioned on Maple Syrup & Madagascar Vanilla Beans.

Gather with friends, grab a boot of Festbier, and with a slap of the foam, let the festivities begin. Crafted with an authentic German recipe, this Marzen-Style Lager is a perfect balance of subtly sweet and refreshingly smooth.

beer.beer_name: Milk of the Murder Hornet - Passion Fruit
beer.beer_description: Milkshake IIPA w/ Mosaic hops, Lactose, Vanilla, and Passionfruit. This one is another new addition to our Milkshake series, with the passionfruit lending a hint of citrusy tartness.

Our Barleywine Ale features American and Belgian malts which provide the base of this extraordinary ale. After 12 months in bourbon barrels the award-winning Straight Jacket® emerges with notes of stone fruit, toasted coconut, molasses, and vanilla coming in waves as you swirl the glass. Enjoy now or store cold.

Ably balanced between its crisp apple base and suite of wintry spices like ginger, clove, cinnamon, and nutmeg, Toasty Cookie Spiced Cider is surprisingly refreshing for something that tastes so much like a cookie.

beer.beer_name: Milk of the Murder Hornet - Strawberry
beer.beer_description: Milkshake IIPA with lactose, strawberry, & vanilla.
Rum barrel coffee imperial stout

beer.beer_name: Bourbon Barrel-Aged No S'more Imperial Stout
beer.beer_description: Barrel-aged chocolate, vanilla, and smoke.
This giant stout is as dark as night.  Rich and smooth, perfect for aging or drinking fresh.
Light English porter. Notes of roasted malt and toffee.

Sometimes, the English language just doesn’t have a word for something. There are words like YOLO, twerk, and OMG, but for some reason there isn’t a plural word for “you.” Sorry, but “ya’ll” or “youse” or even “you guys” doesn’t quite fill the lexical gap. Our Lexical Gap IPA is straight west coast, you guys (see what we did there?). Brewed with massive amounts of Citra, Centennial, Simcoe, and Columbus hops, finding a word to describe your gratification might be pretty tough. Most expletives, however, will probably suffice.

BACK TO BACK GABF MEDALS. 2019 GABF Gold Medal & 2020 GABF Bronze Medal. Our American Lager is brewed with 6 row and 2 row malted barley, midwestern corn, and clear Land of Lincoln water. Simplicity is the peak of civilization. That's that. Stay learned. Do some lite thinking.

Michigan didn't invent old-fashioned fudge, but it was perfected here. We pay tribute to this time-honored tradition with KBS Maple Mackinac Fudge. By amplifying the rich chocolate notes of KBS using Mackinac Fudge coffee, then adding maple syrup and aging it in oak bourbon barrels, we've created a bold new take on our barrel-aged classic - one that could only have originated in Michigan.

Our Robust Porter was sent to a bright tank and infused with a blend of whole bean coffee from one of three nearby neighbors: Sip of Hope, Dark Matter, and Metropolis. The cold-aging allows us to extract the aromatic oils from the coffee without extracting any additional bitterness.

Caramella or ‘candy’ in Italian is a wheatwine aged in Larceny Wheated Bourbon barrels with apple, cinnamon, and natural caramel flavor added after aging. Just like last year, the sweet smoothness from the Larceny Wheated Bourbon barrels adds a lingering warmth that complements the added flavor nuance. It’s nostalgia-inducing flavors are reminiscent of a caramel apple. Our Lead Lab Analyst, Joey Tidei, created this variant as a tribute to his love of seasonal flavors. This luscious embodiment of caramel perfectly paired with a slightly-tart apple flavor will transport you to a crisp Autumn day.
Bourbon County Brand Stout blended with pistachios, cacao, candied Amarena cherries, and natural vanilla flavors.

Bourbon County Special #4 Stout is an oatmeal stout variant of our original Bourbon County Stout recipe, also aged in bourbon barrels, that uses crystal oats to add a nutty character and a smooth mouthfeel. After barrel aging, we added Intelligentsia Coffee, both their cold coffee and single origin coffee beans from Ethiopia, called “Metad Buku,” to bring out a pleasant fruity coffee character. Lastly bourbon barrel-aged maple syrup from Bissell Maple Farm in Ohio is added which provides complexity to the nutty oats and coffee to round out the flavors, ultimately reminiscent of your breakfast ‘special’ at the local diner.
An American style Barleywine brewed in collaboration with our friends at Perennial Artisan Ales. Notes of caramel, nuttiness, and fruity esters.
Imperial stout aged in bourbon barrels with blueberry juice and almond extract added.

beer.beer_name: Bourbon County Brand Kentucky Fog Stout (2020)
beer.beer_description: We’re excited to debut our first-ever tea-inspired variant. Brewer Paul Cade brought this idea to life, inspired by his girlfriend, Martha, who prefers tea over coffee. Our Bourbon County Kentucky Fog Stout is a take on the London Fog tea drink. With that flavor profile in mind, we added Earl Grey Tea and Black Tea from Kilogram Tea, as well as clover honey from The Honey House, to make a Bourbon County Stout variant with a complexity like none before. Trust us, you’ll just have to try it

This beer taught us that patience truly is a virtue. KBS is a big imperial stout brewed with a massive amount of coffee and chocolate and then bourbon barrel-aged to perfection. Incredibly silky and full-bodied with notes of vanilla, cocoa, roasted coffee and charred oak.

The Original Bourbon Barrel aged Imperial Stout. Our primary focus every year is to make this beer the best that it’s ever been, with the best ingredients, which includes the finest of bourbon whiskey barrels. This year’s Bourbon County Stout is aged in a mix of bourbon barrels from a variety of whiskey distilleries. Barrel-aged for a year to develop the complexity that only time can provide, Bourbon County Stout boasts a unique blend of flavors such as fudge, vanilla and caramel — topped off with a rich, complex mouthfeel.
A HUGE Imperial Stout that weighs in at an impressive 12% ABV! As if that's not enough, we added pounds of coffee for a little extra kick.

Born a double-mashed imperial brown ale, then matured for 18 months in freshly drained 10-year Canadian rye whisky barrels, the beer features checkered notes of rich vanilla, charred oak, warming whisky and spicy rye. With a lingering, boozy sweetness and round, resonant flavor, Plaid Habit clearly earns its name.

One of Michael Jackson’s 500 Classic Brews. Carnegie Porter was brewed for the first time in 1836 and tastes the same today as it did then. Carnegie Porter has a creamy head with a scent of coffee. Its sweet and well rounded flavor is balanced by the bitterness of the hops. Storage helps the flavor mature and enhances its harmony.
A soaring wave of lush ripe peach, elevated by a naturally tart finish. A thirst-quenching declaration for when you want to amplify your voice.
Brewed with Cinnamon & Maple Syrup & Milk Sugar

If you’ve ever spent time in a German Beer Garden, you know how much they love their wheat beer.  Our Bavarian-style Hefeweizen is a satisfying blend of sweet wheat and pale malts, clove and banana aromatics, and the zesty tang of wheat beer yeast.
Peanut butter chocolate stout
A perfect formula makes for an easy choice as fruity and citrusy hops lead the way in this IPA.  Our proprietary HopVic technology drives big hop flavor with notes of tangerine and mandarin orange.
Tastes like freshly cut melons and the California sun right in your hand. This light, crisp Wheat Ale is bursting with watermelon, honeydew, and cantalope flavors, finishing bright and refreshing.
Brewed with Blake’s fresh Cinnamon donuts
Modelo Chelada Tamarindo Picante Mexican Beer combines the flavors of lime, tomato, salt and chipotle peppers with tamarind for a spicy yet pleasantly sweet taste in a ready-to-drink can.
Ripe, juicy mango with hints of coconut and pineapple.

We've taken our classic bourbon barrel aged Cherry Stout and artfully entwined it with vanilla. This luscious and dark libation is awash with the tartness of real Wisconsin cherries, smoothed out with soft hints of vanilla.
sour ale rested on blueberries, graham cracker, vanilla, milk sugar and lemon zest
Delight in the delicate taste of fresh Watermelon. This sweet and refreshing flavor is complemented by the pure refreshment of White Claw® Hard Seltzer.

A tropical twist of mango mixed with juicy lemonade and refreshing seltzer.

Truly Lemonade is the perfect mix of refreshing hard seltzer and sweet lemonade that’s big on taste and low on calories. It packs the sweetness of real lemonade with the refreshment of Truly Hard Seltzer.

The Lo Rez Berliner Weisse is back! This time with mango and chile. The heat is low and hits quickly and does not build. The mango balances on the backend. Berliner Weisse funk and tart wheatiness all the way through. Delicious spring/summer quencher.
Imperial stout fermented with almond flour, cacao nibs, cinnamon sticks, vanilla beans, ancho chilies, guajillo chilies, habanero chilies, and cherrywood.
Imperial Stout with coffee, hazelnut, and maple syrup

beer.beer_name: Bananas Foster Imperial Stout (All Canned Dates)
beer.beer_description: Imperial stout with cinnamon, maple, vanilla and banana. Brewed in collaboration with our friends at Crafted 1979 in Mokena, IL.
Imperial stout with almond, walnut, chocolate, marshmallow, vanilla, and lactose.
Imperial Stout fermented with cinnamon, maple syrup, vanilla and lactose.

Like a fine port, Old Stock Ale is intended to be laid down. With an original gravity of over 1.100 and a generous hopping rate, Old Stock Ale is well-designed to round out and mellow with age. It's brewed with classic Maris Otter malt and Fuggles and East Kent Goldings hops, all imported from England.

beer.beer_name: Milk of the Murder Hornet (All Canned Dates)
beer.beer_description: DDH Hazy Imperial IPA w/ Galaxy hops and Lactose

beer.beer_name: Bourbon County Brand Regal Rye Stout (2015)
beer.beer_description: The brewery opted for blackberry juice sourced from Valley Processing, in Sunnyside, Wash., instead of whole fruit both because it’s easier to use as an ingredient and for its richer flavor. The cherries used in Regal Rye are Luxardo cocktail cherries; the beer also incorporates the cherries' bright, sugary syrup. The sea salt “adds another layer that will make the flavors pop slightly — depth to something that’s already deep,

A Norman-style cidre brut, aged in French oak barrels. Reminiscent of the old days in France, before the great wars, when wine makers of the south shared their used barrels with their northern cousins, the resulting ciders were a little bit rough, unfiltered with a balance of flavors from the fruit, the farm and the barrel. Virtue has recreated this traditional cider by sourcing tart fruit, patiently aging for months in wine barrels, and serving as is, without fine filtration. Lapinette is a window into our past, a very tasty time indeed.

Inspired by visits to English country pubs, Honker’s Ale combines a fruity hop aroma with a rich malt middle to create a perfectly balanced beer. Immensely drinkable, Honker’s Ale is not only the beer you can trust but one you’ll look forward to time and again.
Brewed with cocoa nibs, Dutch cocoa powder, and milk sugar. Collab with 8Bit Chocolate.
Kettle-Soured Ale brewed with mango, peach, and milk sugar, and hopped with Hallertau Blanc.

beer.beer_name: All For One, One For All
beer.beer_description: Brewed with hazelnut, vanilla bean, coffee, and milk sugar. Brewed to benefit My Block, My Hood, My City.

As the leaves begin to change and the weather cools, Ichabod makes his annual return from Sleepy Hollow. Ichabod is named after the classic Washington Irving tale, and has the taste of pumpkin, cinnamon, and nutmeg in every sip.

With welcoming notes of dark chocolate and coffee, this Oatmeal Milk Stout combines a variety of roasted grains to produce a complex yet mellow flavor. Fat Pug is rounded out with sweetness provided by lactose and is named in honor of our brewer Adam’s pug, Otto.

2017 GABF Medalist - Oatmeal Milk Stout

An unfiltered rice beer, Màkku is a modern take on Korea’s oldest alcoholic beverage, Makgeolli. For the first time drinker, Màkku is an unanticipated and new experience.
For Màkku Mango, we take 100% pureed mangos and blend it into our original Màkku for a smooth mango fizzy alcohol.
This dry-hopped Hazy Juicy IPA explodes as tropical and fruity elements float through cloudy formations to elevate hops to the highest pedestal.
Imperial milk stout with Madagascar vanilla and a hint of caramel and vanilla flavor.
The rich vanilla and chocolate notes of Dragon’s Milk with the layered flavor of Vanilla Chai – it’s so unique and so complementary.

Colour and sight: Deep dark red colour, with a light pink, compact and lacing head.
Scent: Soft fruity aroma, with hints of almond and mildly sour cherries.
Flavour: Sweet and fruity, with a nice balance between sweet and sour. An excellent dessert beer.
A German Hefeweizen brewed with Wild Strawberry and Urban Till Basil. Light, refreshing and slightly tart.

This creation is a tribute to the founder of Oud Beersel who founded the brewery 135 years ago in 1882. It is a unique blend of Lambic matured a year on Tuscan foudres in Italy, previously used for 30 years for the maturation of the famous wine Brunello di Montalcino and with Lambic of three years matured on an old foudre of Oud Beersel. This exceptional Gueuze is touched by mature red wine on bottles of 37,5 cl and is available in limited quantities. Serve at 8-12 ° C Ingredients: water, barley malt, wheat, hops 6.5% ABV Color: amber gold Aroma: a deep explosion of vinous character with a typical odor of wild yeasts Taste: the pleasant bitterness of pink pampiemousse Combined with a taste of red wine refined in oak casks results in a sour character but well rounded.
Fruity notes from imported Belgian yeast swirl through a precise souring.  Pucker up to a bite of citrus laden tang ending with a delectable experience.
Imperial stout brewed with chili powder, ginger powder, sichuan pepper powder, sea salt and peanut extract
Scotch ale aged for 12 months in Buffalo Trace bourbon barrels and paired with a rich sweet malt, toffee and caramel backbone.
Invited to brew in the US I wanted to use local ingredients. Agamemnon is an Imperial Stout brewed with maple syrup. Boiled 7 hours.

Blackwater™ Series is a fusion of exotic flavors, making each a perfect pairing when you are craving an exceptional stout full of personality. White Chocolate Raspberry balances creamy sweetness with a touch of tart fruit. Super smooth and glowing pink, indulge in this dessert in a glass.
Southern Tier’s Blackwater Series unleashes its popular flavor Crème Brûlée in NITRO. With notes of vanilla and caramel, this stout is sweet, creamy and uncannily true to the namesake dessert.

English style barleywine aged in Angel's Envy bourbon barrels. Brewed with enough Maris Otter pale, Aromatic and caramel malts to nearly overflow our mash tun.  We then balanced this beer with some English Nugget and Kent Goldings hops.  The resulting ale was sweet, nutty and powerful, but we didn't stop there.  The entire batch was put into used Angel's Envy barrels for nearly 3 months to gather the residual bourbon flavor and some aromatic and drying oak notes.  By the way, Balling is a measurement of specific gravity.

Unlock the Vault, our barrel series committed to the careful, prolonged conditioning and blending of barrel-aged ales. This crisp golden ale unites lemon, orange peel and coriander spices with flavorful Belgian esters, which blend brilliantly with bright, tangy notes of peach brandy barrels. Enjoy immediately or store under lock and key.
Six Foot Strawberry Blonde is our Six Foot Blonde base recipe with real strawberry flavoring added post-fermentation in conditioning tanks.
Bursting with notes of tropical fruit, Son of Juice features loads of Mosaic, Simcoe and Nugget hops. Pilsner malt and oats lend to a soft body and touch of haze, making for a juicy, low-bitter IPA.
Aged in Buffalo Trace barrels
Kitchen Sink Porter (chocolate, brown sugar, molasses, licorice, chili peppers).
Mixed Berry flavored Hard Seltzer
Lizard King is light, crisp and refreshing. Mosaic hops make for one tropical, citrusy, and piney pale that gets our mojo risin’.
A delectable stout with coffee, maple syrup, and bacon with rye malt added, and then aged in Rye Whiskey Barrels.

Aged in a series of American Oak foeders using a blending technique known as Solera, nuanced flavors of caramel, toffee & fig create an experience made to be savored. This legendary ale will continue to evolve with each pull from the foeders, becoming more complex over time.
A robust sour ale aged in bourbon barrels and then aged on fresh, locally grown cherries.

The 2006 and 2008 World Beer Cup competition resulted in Silver Medals for our Scottish Ale. The number one selling beer at Shoreline, Beltaine celebrates the start of spring each year on May 1st. In Scotland, participants of the pagan festival typically run around communal fires naked and take home some
of the fire to their hearths. A rich amber color and hints of caramel, make this beer
extremely easy drinking.

beer.beer_name: Lost Sailor Imperial Stout Barrel Aged Series

beer.beer_description: This Spiced Saison will likely become a true love of yours; parsley, sage, rosemary, and thyme, + lemon juice.  Remember beer to one who lives there.

You will find yourself please-and-thanking this Dunkelweizen. Smooth chocolate floats above bready Munich malts with a huge percentage of pillowy wheat. Subtle notes if banana and clove from the Belgian wheat yeast add a lovely complexity

Deep dark brown color with a tan head, this stout boasts a complex grain bill of dark malt that 
contributes to its bold roasty flavor with subtle notes of chocolate.
A light blonde ale, golden in color and a delicate maltiness. We have added peach to give it a unique fruit flavor that gors great with summer.
All pilsner malt creates a biscuit-like flavor, perfectly balanced with an earthiness from traditional German noble hops.
A decadent imperial version of our classic Chocolate Stout made with imported Dutch bittersweet chocolate.

St.Bernardus Tripel is a traditional abbey ale brewed in the classic "Triple" style of Belgium's best Abbey Ales. It has a blond to pale amber color with a wonderful head, slightly sweet aroma and the orangey-grassy flavors of hops in the finish. Wonderfully drinkable and surprisingly light (8,0% ABV).
Imperial Porter brewed with Roasted Peanuts, Peanut Butter, Mexican cacao, Milk Sugar & Caramel, in collaboration with our friends at Smallcakes Aurora.

2017 GABF SILVER MEDAL WINNER.
Mamoot is the brown ale’s laid back brother, a perfect breakfast beer. Subtle notes of jam, coffee, and chocolate add to the toasty finish. This brew is mahogany colored and full flavored, despite the relatively light ABV.
Mamoot is great with BBQ, frog legs and beef jerky.  Mamoot and Gouda cheese is a fine afternoon snack.
2017 GABF SILVER MEDAL WINNER.
2016 BEST OF CRAFT BEER SILVER MEDAL.
2015 GABF BRONZE MEDAL WINNER.
2014 GABF SILVER MEDAL WINNER.
Imperial stout with hazelnuts, walnuts, almonds, pistachios.
Milk Stout with cacao nibs and milk sugar
American Wild Ale with Peaches

A second sticky hit from 420 Strain, an American Wheat packed with herbal, juicy mango notes and a distinctive dank nose. Strain specific terpenes and natural hemp-type flavors complement the hop and malt bill, delivering a euphoric ale with that fresh olfactory bonus rip.
Sunshine-colored with haze for days, this IPA boasts a juicy, tropical fruit hop aroma with a massive orange-citrus hop flavor.

Our Raspberry Hefeweizen is a true fruit beer, not a fruit-flavored beer.  We add pureed raspberries to our Hefeweizen during the primary fermentation process.  Although we add no sugar, color or flavors, the resulting beer is a hazy pink color, with citrus aromas from the wheat and a flavor that is neat and tart.  While this beer is low in bitterness, it is not overwhelmingly sweet, making it a thoroughly drinkable beer for the season.

A smooth refreshing lager fermented and aged for five weeks at cold temperatures to yield its exceptionally smooth flavor. A delicate, slightly spicy hop aroma complements the malty body of this beer.

Imperial Stout brewed with Ugandan Coffee, Ghanaian & Mexican Cacao Nibs, and Saigon Cinnamon. Brewed in collaboration with Church Street Brewing Co., for the Black is Beautiful project hosted by Weathered Souls Brewing Co. in San Antonio, TX.

Inspired by the brothers time living in France, this food-friendly ale is deep amber in color, with a toasty and sweet caramel start. It finishes with just enough hops to clean off the palate. Bon appetit!

Way smooth and silky with a nice wheatly-esque-ish-ness. A truly unique style featuring a strong hop finish on a silky body. A hoppy pale wheat ale that is great for IPA fans but so smooth that the hefeweizen fans dig it too.

Produced in the tradition of 18th Century English brewers who supplied the court of Russia’s Catherine the Great, Old Rasputin seems to develop a cult following wherever it goes. It’s a rich, intense brew with big complex flavors and a warming finish.

Breakfast is the most important meal of the day, many say, and if you are a beer geek there is no better way to start the day than with a powerful, complex morning stout.

This is the beer that started it all for Mikkeller. Oatmeal Stout brewed with coffee and seven different kind of malt (Pils, Oat, Smoked, Caramunich, Brown, Pale Chocolate, Chocolate), roasted barley, oat flakes, hops (Centennial, Cascade), American ale yeast and gourmet coffee. Aroma is a combination of malts, caramel, chocolate and coffee. The body is medium with light coffee and chocolate flavors with a creamy texture, average carbonation and a bitter edge on the finish. A beer that goes extremely well with breakfast.
Apple Cider with Hibiscus and Rose Hips

Meet Mexican Honey Light, a lighter kind of buzz. This bright and clean cerveza is brewed with orange blossom honey straight from orange groves south of the border, Amarillo hops and a twist of citrus. Our new, more sessionable spin on Mexican Honey is refreshingly crushable and brewed to take it easy, anytime, anywhere.

An unfiltered, unfettered, unprecedented brown ale aged in handmade wooden brewing vessels. The caramel and vanilla complexity unique to this beer comes from the exotic Paraguayan Palo Santo wood from which these tanks were crafted. Palo Santo means "holy tree" and its wood has been used in South American wine-making communities.
Beerlao is brewed from the best local rice and high quality malt from Europe, giving it a unique taste. Since its launchin 1973, Beerlao has become the bestselling and leading brand in Laos.
Imperial Stout featuring rich roasted chocolate malts was aged in our Mezcal barrels.
Imperial stout aged in whiskey barrels

A smoothie-style beer infused with actual mango, actual vanilla bean, & lactose.

Malts: Domestic Pale, Malted Oats

Hops: Warrior (United States)

Yeast: American Ale

And: Mango, Vanilla, Lactose, Dextrose (not vegan)

Strong, balanced, stone fruit. Venn's take on an American Strong Ale.

Malts: Golden Promise, Victory

Hops: Warrior, Chinook, Amarillo, Cascade

Yeast: British Ale

And: Dextrose

An imperial kettle sour that tastes like Hawaiian Punch! Infused with papaya, pink guava, blood orange, passion fruit, & pineapple.

Malts: 2-Row, White Wheat, Unmalted White Wheat

Hops: none

Yeast: Lactobacillus, Champagne

And: Papaya, Pink Guava, Apricot, Blood Orange, Passion Fruit, Pineapple, Dextrose

A Venn-style kettle sour, infused with actual blackberry, raspberry, & boysenberry. Previously called "Triple Berry Sour".

Malts: Domestic Pale, White Wheat, Unmalted White Wheat

Hops: none

Yeast: Champagne, Lactobacillus

And: Blackberries, Raspberries, Boysenberries

A Venn-style kettle sour infused with actual blackberries & actual mango.

Malts: Domestic Pale, White Wheat, Unmalted White Wheat

Hops: none

Yeast: Champagne, Lactobacillus

And: Blackberries, Mango

This easy drinking IPA is loaded up with four varieties of American grown hops. Fruity flavors of pear and peach play off of resinous, piney notes. Belgian crystal malt complements the bitterness for a well-balanced IPA.
Pairs well with spicy food of all sorts and sweet desserts.  Drink a Snapper while munching on a nice ripe cheese.
100% of proceeds being donated to: The Innocence Project of Minnesota, Joyce Preschool, ABEP & Pimento Relief Fund, Du Nord Recovery Fund

beer.beer_name: No. 49 City Girl Cold Press Stout

beer.beer_description: Golden haze; spicy, tangerine, peach aromas; banana/bubble gum/clove-like spices, fruity esters; warming alcohol flavors; medium body.
Golden-colored ale is sweet, yet refreshing; offers a pleasant blueberry aroma and complemented by fruity ale yeast character; little hop character present; medium body.

Brewed to taste just like a Moscow Mule, this beer shouts “GINGER” on the nose with a light, fresh citrus lime balancing out the ginger in the flavor. Poured straight into the pint or over ice, this beer tastes best in the sunshine and warm weather.

Lookout is a refreshing American Pale Ale with an orange blossom hop character and a clean malt body. The perfect companion for piloting a river.
Pairs well with everything.  Seriously, everything. We especially like drinking Lookout at BBQs, on float trips, golf courses and while tending our gardens.
Imperial Stout conditioned on 300 shots of Matador espresso from Up Coffee Roasters.

beer.beer_name: Punk Tacos: Acai And Blue Agave
beer.beer_description: Fruited IPA hopped with Centennial, Cascade and Amarillo. Referemented with Acai and Blue Agave syrup.

Shiphead is brewed with Peruvian ginger straight out of the rainforest. Coriander and fresh lemon zest yield citrus tang. Alien Sea Sorceress, find your glow.
Shiphead pairs great with Asian food, salads, and popsicles.

This unique cider combines a dry cider base with tart Michigan cherry juice. Pouring a lovely shade of red, this snappy cider features an unexpectedly creamy mouthfeel. A refreshing departure from sweeter fruited cider and a cider that fans of sour beer will love.
We take our normal dry cider, blend it with seltzer water and other natural flavors to create a lower calorie, lower alcohol, easy drinking cider.
IPA
The Black is Beautiful initiative is a collaborative effort amongst the brewing community and its customers, in an attempt to bring awareness to the injustices that many people face daily.
Aurora Amber is an American Amber Ale, solidly focused on its malt character with caramel and toffee notes, hopped with Styrian Aurora hops.

We’re all familiar with Belgian Dubbels and Tripels, but what about the Single? Sometimes you’re just trying to get on first.  A lighter, hoppier version of a Belgian Tripel, the Single (also called an Abbey Ale) delivers all the Belgian-ey goodness you’d expect without the high booze content.

An alternative to dark and heavy winter warmers and stouts, Bright White (formerly Winter White) is a stylish and refreshing Wheat Ale.

Fermented with a Belgian ale yeast, this blend of barley and wheat malts yields a mixture of clove and fruity aromas, all without the use of any spices.

An unfiltered lemon-wheat ale that drinks like a shandy, but gives you those NEIPA characteristics. We add a ton of lemon puree during fermentation and top it off with just enough Citra to provide some hop brightness. A small amount of lactose is added to the boil to add some residual sweetness. Summer in a glass.
A refreshing citrus ale, Tangerine Wheat combines our Lost Coast Harvest Wheat with natural Tangerine flavors. Brewed with a combination of wheat and crystal malts and finished with Perle hops.

Burning Bridges w/ vanilla is an English-inspired brown ale: Toasty, bittersweet, and elegant. Roasty flavors meld with chocolate with caramel notes, balanced by a subtle Cascade hop bitterness and gentle vanilla accent.
Our beloved Southy aged on Vanilla beans.
This Imperial IPA is truly heavenly; we hop it intensely, and then balance it with local honey for a result that's both powerful and extremely drinkable.
Drunk Monk Belgian Golden Strong Ale with Rum

The Roman Empire had a certain ‘je ne sais quoi’ – festive food culture, extravagant architecture and spectacular live entertainment. Some might argue the Emperors where brutal, mad and hungry for power, and the people vain when taking baths and working out all day. Listen – that’s still all part of the secret Imperial ingredient – keep it cool, clean, confident, arrogant and flamboyant. Forza Imperiale.

The amazing taste of peanut butter from a spoon has long been thought of as the peak of taste bud euphoria. That was before you got your paws on Wet Snout Peanut Butter Stout. Smooth and creamy peanut butter blends perfectly with chocolate and malt notes for a treat like no other.

We pay homage to the American novelist, Eleanor Porter, who introduced “Pollyanna” to the world way back in 1913. Eleanor is a full-bodied and layered, robust porter brewed with Belgian caramel malts, American chocolate malts, German hops, and English yeast. This beer is heavy on the rich, dark chocolates with lots of caramelized raisins and caramel, but perfectly balanced with a distinct coffee flavor and moderate hop bitterness.
Milk stout brewed with milk sugar and cocoa nibs.

This world famous bock from Bavaria’s Holy Mountain is not meant to be rushed, but savoured slowly. As solid as a rock, Andechser Doppelbock Dunkel presides over the evening meal with a colour reminiscent of dark copper with nuances of fiery red. Its clear gleaming look harmonises with its firm, fine pored head. 

Also the aroma delights the connoisseur: soft roasted accents and a nuance of dried fruit carrying a vein of caramel. This Doppelbock Dunkel from Bavaria’s Holy Mountain presents a pleasant effervescence. And then there’s the unmistakable flavour: mouthcoating and velvety, strong and yet pleasantly malty – a powerful, robust body. At the same time, it develops an easily recognisable sweetness, embraced in roasted cocoa and a light, bitter hoppiness. 

Concluding with a powerful punch, this Doppelbock departs with a lingering aftertaste of quality plain chocolate. A strong Doppelbock that embodies the centuries old Benedictine brewing tradition, sip by delicious sip.

The color and scent of a summer afternoon; now with a mango twist. This limited release of your favorite summer beer just got a blast of real fruit. It's refreshing, easy-drinking and only here for a short time.

Hazy “Adventure” IPA with Vic Secret and Enigma  
99 Calories 

Don’t call it a light beer. Just 4% ABV and 99 calories, but dry-hopped and brewed like those haze bombs people wait in line for. But we know you... you’re not standing around waiting in line—you’re hiking up mountains and forging ahead to the next adventure. Blaze your trail with some haze that can actually keep up.

Although they were painfully humiliated when they came to brew with us a couple of years ago - an episode that would later be known as "The Great, Big Kentucky Sausage Fest" - the friendly dudes of Against The Grain Brewery were kind enough to invite us in for a second round of brewing when Morten and Jacob of Amager Bryghus last visited the US. In spite of a house in mayhem - ATG was in the midst of constructing a new brewery AND some crazy Scotsmen from a company named Brewdog were running around making a lot of noise - big Sam Cruz and his cohorts were all their usual calm, kind and hospitable selves, as Southern folks are. We ended up brewing a somewhat unusual style, an Imperial Rye lager - rustic and robust - of course with a more tha

Lambickx De Troch has a heady aroma of grass, peaches and sour apples with a hint of smoke and is anchored by a dash sweet hay flavor. The brewery’s delicate aging process produces a beer that is big in flavor, with a round acidity and citrus-forward notes of lemon, tangerine and grapefruit. The bold flavors soften into a rich, sour-sweet finish laced with tannic wood notes. Not quite still, Lambickx De Troch has just the slightest hint of carbonation. This wine-like gem is a perfect companion to food, playing nicely with citrus-laced poultry dishes like apricot demi-glazed chicken and fresh shellfish meals like mussels in white wine, crab cakes or creamy pastas.

Corona Hard Seltzer is a tasty, spiked sparkling water with a splash of natural fruit flavor that allows you to relax and enjoy the moment. Relax responsibly®. Corona® Hard Seltzer Spiked Sparkling Water with Natural Flavors. Imported by Crown Imports, Chicago, IL *Not a low-calorie food. Per 12 fl. oz. serving average analysis: Calories 90, Carbs 0 grams, Protein 0 grams, Fat 0 grams
IPA brewed with Amarillo and Cascade. In the mouth and nose prevail citrus and exotic fruits. The bitter end and make it a balanced beer for hop lovers ...

Discover the only hard seltzer that gives you that day-at-the-beach feeling, wherever the day takes you. Corona Hard Seltzer is a tasty, spiked sparkling water with a splash of natural fruit flavor that allows you to relax and enjoy the moment. Corona Hard Seltzer is the only hard seltzer brand with 0g carbs, 0g sugars* and Corona's chill attitude along with all the other benefits you expect from a hard seltzer like 90 calories, natural flavors, and gluten-free. Relax responsibly®. Corona® Hard Seltzer Spiked Sparkling Water with Natural Flavors. Imported by Crown Imports, Chicago, IL *Not a low-calorie food. Easy to drink with a lingering, pleasant aftertaste. A rich, yolky-orange wheat beer, featuring the aroma of clove and fruit in perfect balance; refreshing on a warm day, with a hint of mandarin-orange-like acidity; huge effervescent head. Thick lasting foam that leaves an attractive lacing after every sip.
Refreshing, medium-bodied, with an aroma of grain and the pleasant floral and citrus of Saphir hops.

First we started with our classic export stout made with a blend of American and British roasted malts. Giving you that classic roasty, coffee, and dark chocolate flavors. Then we added in lots of cocoa nibs, coconut, lactose, and vanilla beans to recreate those flavors of German chocolate cake. One sip will make you think it's your birthday.
Stout with peanut butter lactose and chocolate. Make to replicate a Reese Peanut Butter cup

This ancient beer style dates back to medieval times and is rarely made today. Made with large percentage of rye and hefeweizen yeast gives it notes of spicy rye, caramel, clove, and hints of banana. Truly a unique beer.
Pale Wheat Ale with gummy bears. Very Bear-ie. Minimal bitterness to emphasize the gummy goodness. Made with 120 lbs of Haribo Gummy Bears. This light based ale is full of fruity flavors.

beer.beer_name: For Goodness Shakes Tropical Fruit Milkshake
beer.beer_description: Variant of our milkshake IPA series. This one has mango, passion fruit, pineapple, orange, guava, and lactose.

beer.beer_name: Guava Margarita Gose (We Want the Funk)
beer.beer_description: Another version of our margarita gose series. This one we added 300 lbs of guava purée. We upped the salt a dash too. You’ll think you sippin this on a carribean island.
Conditioned on Urfa biber chile flakes, dried Aleppo chile pepper, vanilla beans, and cinnamon.
Buffalo Trace barrels for 10 months.
An American west coast Pale Ale chock full of dank, aromatic hops that bite up front, then ease into citrus, and set the finish up to nail the spot.
Kolsch lightly hopped with New Zealand hops, Waimea and The Bruce

Crown Hut is a mixed culture wheat lager aged 4 months in oak and blended onto fresh lime peel. Bottled in clear glass to encourage that classic light-struck character, there's a slight wheat sweetness, hints of kiwi and white grape, with a margarita level dose of lime.

Space Camper Cosmic IPA is an exhilarating initiation into a mind-bending alternate universe of India Pale Ales. Our brewers employ massive hop additions at the end of the boil, and during fermentation, to minimize upfront bitterness and create a juicy IPA bursting with tropical fruit flavors and aromas of nectar and citrus.

The cocktail inspiration lives on. Our imperial gose is brewed with agave and sea salt before being aged in tequila barrels. But it doesn’t end there. Once it’s pulled from the barrels, it gets a dose of fresh grapefruit juice to ramp up the tanginess and to pay homage to our other favorite tequila-based cocktail, the Paloma. Sweet, salty, and mouth-puckeringly delicious. ¡Más Agave... Grapefruit!

Straight from Zee Wickel is our take on a Zwickelbier lager.  A Zwickelbier is an unfiltered lager often sampled through a zwickel (sample valve) on a lagering tank.  We modeled the beer around a Czech Pilsner featuring a noble spicy hop aroma from Michigan grown Zuper Saazer and a soft bitterness from German Magnum.
Witbier brewed with grapefruit, coriander, and pink peppercorns.
This Imperial Rye Stout was aged in Buffalo Trace Bourbon barrels for 13 months with an addition of Cholaca liquid chocolate
60% Wheat grain bill for a wheat wine aged in Buffalo Trace bourbon barrels for 1 year

Subtly sour and a little sweet, this ale is a refreshing take on a nearly extinct German style, gose. Watermelon is the highlight of this lightly-hopped treat and gives it a hint of satisfying juiciness. The soft mouthfeel and dry finish comes courtesy of the addition of sea salt, a traditional gose ingredient.

Inspired by the classic Dutch cookie best enjoyed with a cup of coffee. Our brewers used rich caramel, vanilla, cinnamon, and freshly roasted coffee beans to bring that experience to our signature bourbon barrel-aged stout.
sour ale with (L)actose, (G)uava, (B)lackberry, (T)angerine, (Q)uince + rainbow sprinkles
Lemon shandy wheat beer. Light in body and color, this traditional favorite is light and lemony, perfect for a summer afternoon in the sun.

beer.beer_name: Dragon’s Milk Reserve: Scotch Barrel-Aged Stout With Marshmallow & Dark Chocolate (2020-2)
beer.beer_description: One of our favorite places to share a Dragon’s Milk is around the campfire, and this brew pays tribute to those legendary summer nights. A blend of Highland and Speyside Scotch barrels bring just a hint of peated smokiness that accentuate the roasted notes of our signature stout, while toasted marshmallow aroma and flavors set the stage for a rich, chocolatey finish.

Baseball, fireworks and stout - that’s what Chicago summer is all about. Maybe not in 2020, but if we add some coconut, now we have a party. Flavors of chocolate and coconut are at the forefront. The creamy mouthfeel leads to more chocolate and coconut with some espresso notes in the finish.
Papaya pineapple with a tangerine finisg
One of our very first brews. Light bodied American Wheat Ale featuring truckloads of Galaxy hops. Expect strong notes of passion fruit.
Low ABV, lightly bittered IPA with tons of flavor. Loaded with citrus fruit flavors of lemon, lime, and orange that give way to a fruity finish with a hint of bitter orange.
Wobble IPA is golden in color with subtle malt character, big complex citrus and piney hop notes throughout, subtle alcohol

Using three of our favorites – Amarillo, Mosaic and Simcoe – this juicy, hazy New England-style IPA is bursting with all those hop notes you know and love like citrus and tropical fruits, with just a hint of bitterness for a balanced finish. Get ready to spread the love.

Coffee Orange Porter

One day we received an email from the Mikkeller HQ saying that they had an American gentleman coming to Copenhagen. The name of this gentleman was Mr. Drew Fox who not only happened to have his own brewery close to Chicago back home, but who also would love to come visit Amager Bryghus to brew a beer. That kind of proposal is simply impossible to turn down, so we found an open slot in our brewing schedule. For quite some time we had been curious about brewing a beer that had both coffee and orange zest, and since Drew has created several excellent coffee beers at his 18th Street Brewery we sat down to create Lawrence of Arabica, a Coffee Orange Porter. A mild and easygoing Porter, with an orange twist. We don’t hesitate to call Drew one of the kindest and friendliest dudes in the craft beer world, and we are honored to have created this beer with him. 

Ingredienser: Vand. Bygmalt: Pilsner, Roasted barley, Caraaroma, Chocolate. Hvedemalt: Flaked wheat, Wheat. Rugmalt: Rye crystal. Humle: Tomahawk, Citra. Kaffe. Tørret appelsinskræl. Gær: UK-ale

"When poured into the glass you will instantly sense that Hr. Frederiksen is a gentleman with both potency and a huge personality. Dark as Hr. Frederiksen's humor, this imperial stout is inspired by the American imperial stouts with it's dense and creamy light brown head that leaves nice lacings in the glass while the head reluctantly dissipates. We are willing to admit that we went crazy with the malts in this beer. A massive 8 different types of malts were used, and it is the dark and heavily roasted ones that give the beer it's color and almost extreme full body - this is almost a meal in a bottle. The bitterness is also delivered by the heavily roasted malts backed up by the American Centennial hops. Oh yes, Hr. Frederiksen is an experience which should be enjoyed slowly, but in return he will last all night warming you with his alcohol and challenging charm. We have named this beer after a good friend, without whom, Amager Bryghus would not be what it is today.
Oud Bruin

ITA: QUANDO LA TERRITORIALITA' E' UN INCANTO
Una delle "birre del territorio" del birrificio. In questo caso l'ingrediente principe sono le radici di genziana che provengono dalla cooperativa Micillo di Consigliano. Le radici sono utilizzate in un'infusione della durata di 2 minuti durante le ultimi fasi della bollitura. La birra al naso è dominata da sentori pepati, di sottobosco e floreali. In bocca il primo impatto è mieloso, seguito da sentori di radici pepe e frutta a polpa gialla. Il retrogusto è delicato ma molt persistente.
ENG: The charming touch of
terroir
One of our ‘terroir’ beers, brewed with
Gentian roots, traditionally used for a
local liqueur, added at the very end of
the boil.
The aromas are peppery, earthy and floral.
The mouthfeel is firstly of honey flavors
then earthy, peppery and yellow fruits.
The finish is delicate and long lasting.

beer.beer_name: The Great, Big Kentucky Sausage Fest
beer.beer_description:
We expected banjos and Bourbon but received nothing of that sort. Instead our brew day with the handsome fellers of Against The Grain Brewery from Louisville, Kentucky turned into a hotdog eating contest. Yep, no kiddin’. Big Kentuckian feller, Sam, challenged our own big feller, Jacob, as to who could down the most gourmet hotdogs, big and spicy as they were with specialty toppings. Well, Sam should never have done that….should you Sam? However, a beer was indeed brewed in between all the trash talk and wieners. We hope you’ll enjoy this hoppy Imperial Brown Ale - it was designed to go with hotdogs in particular and other spicy and smoked foods. 

Ingredients: Water. Malts: Pale, Brown, Melanoidin, Biscuit, Chocolate. Hops: Herkules, Tomahawk, East Kent Goldings, Cascade, Simcoe. Yeast: US-ale.
Bourbon barrel aging marries impressions of vanilla and oak with the rich flavors of roasted barley and coffee in this complex and robust stout.
Light bodied, clean, and bubbly with a delicate light gold hue and soft fruitiness. Try it with blueberry, raspberry, or our syrup of the month.

Hot pHuzz is the 7th annual Bloomington, Indiana brewery collaboration. It features a complex blend of funk, Belgian character, mild heat & subtle sweetness. Belgian wort was aged on peppers & blended with sour blonde ale aged on peaches. It’s balanced and approachable, but also intriguing and layered. An array of different flavors meld together into one cohesive and delicious beer — much like five Bloomington breweries getting together to produce a single one-of-a-kind release. Hot pHuzz is brewed in collaboration with Switchyard Brewing, Bloomington Brewing, Function Brewing, & The Tap.
Adding blood orange to our Yellow Dwarf Dry Hopped American Wheat Ale can only lead to great things! The citrus perfectly complements the fruity and tropical aromas provided by the hops.
Cherry Wheat is an easy drinking American Wheat Ale with a red hue that is racked on sweet and tart cherries.

Northeastern IPAs — also referred to as a New England, juicy, or hazy IPAs — offer incredible aromatics from hop additions during extended whirlpools along with the application of certain dry-hopping techniques.
Hu Dang!’s hops varieties create tropical fruit aromas and provide the balanced hop bitterness sought by IPA lovers.
The fresh flavor of Natural Lime can’t be ignored. Every sip is met with a purely refreshing, zesty citrus aroma and a clean, crisp finish.

Brewed with well water (the original well, sunk in 1758, is still in use with the hard water is drawn from 85 feet underground), the gently roasted organic chocolate malt and organic cocoa impart a delicious, smooth and creamy character, with inviting deep flavours and a delightful finish – this is the perfect marriage of satisfying stout and luxurious chocolate.
