The result is a smooth, decadent and thick bodied beer that hides its 11.2% ABV nicely. Expect notes of semi-sweet chocolate, molasses, coconut chips and roasted malts.

Introducing “GUAVA!” This DIPA was brewed as a hybrid IPA base, a prominent bitter backbone, followed by a swell of juicy hop goodness. Then for good measure topped off with 30 gallons of pink guava puree! Packed full of Idaho 7, Citra & a super fresh batch of simcoe leaves us with a prominent guava, passionfruit, papaya and a subtle vanilla creaminess from the high percentage of wheat!

Crimson Red in Color, Subtle Prickly Pear, Fruity Finish, Floral

Brewed w/ 100% Organic Prickly Pear

Expect lovely, warm smells of single malt scotch, oaky bourbon barrels, smoke, sweet caramel and roasted malts, a bit of earthy spice and a scintilla of dark fruit. It’s a kick-back sipper made to excite the palate.

Distribution Note: Now available year-round beginning April of 2018.

This golden ale bonds fragrant meadowfoam honey, soft vanilla and toasty malt into an ale portfolio that is decadent and diverse. InvEster yields big returns showcasing a special Belgian yeast known for intense flavors (esters) of banana, red fruit and spice. This ale is sure to leave you feeling bullish.

GT's Cannabliss infuses organice & raw Kombucha with hemp CBD (cannabidiol). Harnessing of the goodness of the Earth, this lively, fermented tea offers natural effervescence and billions of living probiotics with 25mg of the highest-quality CBD.

Tripel Karmeliet is still brewed to an authentic beer recipe from 1679 originating in the former Carmelite monastery in Dendermonde. Written over 300 years ago, this recipe describes the use of three kinds of grain: wheat, oats and barley.

The name Tripel karmeliet thus refers both to its origin and its in-bottle refermentation. From many trial brews of multigrain tripels carried out at our brewery in the 90s, it appears that the particular historic combination of the 3 kinds of grain still remains the ideal blend.

beer.beer_name: Drew Curtis / Wil Wheaton / Greg Koch Stone Farking Wheaton w00tstout (2019)
beer.beer_description:
Stout brewed with pecans, wheat & rye, one quarter aged in bourbon barrels.

2019 Edition
Over the years, Stone Farking Wheaton w00tstout has become one of our most anticipated annual releases - and not just because it’s an astoundingly flavorful stout concocted as a collaboration between FARK’s Drew Curtis, nerd royalty Wil Wheaton and Stone Brewing co-founder Greg Koch. It’s the incredible label art adorning this stout over the years that has elevated it to the pinnacle of beer, geekery and beer geekery. This year’s gloriously awesome artwork comes from the talented hands of comic artist Alan Davis, who has worked on some of the most iconic comic book series of all time, including Uncanny X-Men and Justice League of America. His depiction of a hero who channels our iconic gargoyle’s guardian powers to battle against the evils of the world of beer is a fitting representation for this year’s label, and for the relentlessly intense flavor of this intergalactic imperial stout inside.
Aged in Kentucky whiskey barrels for 6 months, this stout boasts roasty flavors and notes of coffee and chocolate. It's rich mouthfeel supports the hint of bourbon and a smooth warming finish.

Pistachios (species P. vera) have been used in culinary applications for thousands of years. For a much shorter period, innovative brewers have used them to add a luscious character to their beers. Our delicate cream ale with Caravienne malt adds a touch more body than some others might. At just over five percent, this is a session beer you’ll want to get crackin’ with.
A rich, roasty porter hopped with Simcoe.

A premium lager beer brewed from the finest ingredients, Singha is a full-bodied 100% barley malt beer that is distinctively rich in taste with strong hop characters. Brewed with three hops: Saaz, Perle and Hallertau. 

Brewed and bottled by Pathumthani Brewery Co. Ltd., Pathumthani, Thailand.

location.brewery_state: กรุงเทพมหานคร

beer.beer_description: 500 years of hard work went into making this beer that features the aroma of orange peel, coriander and herbs that the merry monks imported from sunny Curacao. Speaking of which: pouring Hoegaarden is just like letting the sun fall into your glass: light yellow and naturally murky. And the soft foam adds a cloudy finish. And then there’s the soft taste, light and slightly sweet and sour and with subtle citrus notes… ah, just go ahead and taste it instead of reading about it!

Probably the best beer in the world, and the flagship brand in Carlsberg Group's portfolio. A regular in millions of bars across 140 countries worldwide, it is a truly international beer brand.

Hordeum vulgare. That’s the Latin name for barley, but there’s nothing vulgar about it. In fact, it is a rather special malting barley we use. We have our own Barley Breeding Group, which works in close contact with our brewmasters.

The group selects the barley with the best traits and grows it in our research fields, using only traditional breeding methods, 100% free of genetic modifications. Considering that Carlsberg is made from 100% pure malt i.e. no adjuncts it could take some years before we breed the necessary amount of barley. Probably worth the effort.

Hops are our secret ingredient. Of course it is no secret that we use hops in our beer, but the types we use are prepared according to a secret recipe that’s exclusive to us. It’s called the Carlsberg Aroma Hop Extract and nobody but us at Carlsberg can use it. After all, there can only be one best beer in the world.

Yeast is at the heart of our history. In 1879, Carlsberg was the first brewery to produce a purified brewer’s yeast, the Saccharomyces Carlsbergensis. Since then we’ve been constantly working to improve our yeast’s taste and the stability of our beer. We do it by using a classic breeding method, which means it can take up to 20 trials and several years to obtain a new yeast strain that’s good enough for brewing

Brewed for Singapore and Hongkong with 7.2% abv. 
European tradition. International premium quality. 
Anchor Strong Beer is "Cold Filtered" to give you an easy to drink, quality beer that is fuller and stronger in taste.

Anchor Smooth pilsener beer has been enjoyed for its crisp, smooth and refreshing taste since 1933. Today Anchor is still brewed in the pilsen tradition but with special aromatic European hops to give you an even richer, smoother taste.

In different countries ABV may vary

Brewed in Singapore since 1932, Tiger Beer is a full-flavored, pilsner-style golden lager with a slightly sweet note and an amazingly clean finish. 2010 World Beer Cup Gold Medal (international style lager).

Light in color, silky smooth, and delightedly easy to drink. Set B checks all the boxes of a traditional Witbier. We depart from tradition with the inclusion of bread from Singapore’s oldest bakery, along with freshly zested orange peel to create a traditional beer for the modern world.
Barrel Aged Blend with Cherries, Vanilla, and Chocolate.
a session stout
A bourbon barrel-aged English-style Old Ale commemorating our 11-year anniversary by blending in special barrel-aged reserves from each year leading up to it.

We scoured the hills of the green mountain state to find the perfect maple syrup to complement this barrel-aged imperial stout. Sticky and decadent, with a subtly sweet and big, bold mouthfeel.

Imperial Stout aged in Bourbon Barrels with Maple Syrup.

Michigan Cherry highlights two of our favorite fruits grown in Southwest Michigan: crisp apples, and juicy cherries. Southwest Michigan is one of the top sour cherry-producing regions in the United States. Our Michigan Cherry blends last year's harvest of Michigan apples from local orchards that is aged in French oak barrels. We then add fresh-pressed juice from Michigan cherries.

Working with our friends at Intelligentsia, we flew down to Guatemala to source some of the world's best coffee to use as we release the first-ever Coffee Barleywine. The beer is an English-style Barleywine, meaning malt forward, and aged in 4+ year old Heaven Hill Bourbon barrels before adding La Soledad coffee beans right before packaging to retain a bold coffee aroma and flavor.
Golden Ale aged in bourbon and wine barrels

Toffee and burnt sugar aroma. Flavors of sweet, dried apricots and a mild, earthy bitterness that is the hallmark of hallertau hops. Medium bodied, medium carbonation. A dry, malty body delivers sweet dried fruit flavors complemented with an earthy bitterness.

Proprietor’s Bourbon County Brand Stout is meant to show our immense gratitude to our neighbors here in Chicago – the loyal and adventurous fans whose support helped bring Bourbon County Brand Stout to towering new heights. Each year this release will differ from the previous year; a special variant created for Chicago and unique to the year it was released. Whether your first sip is today or was from that first batch in 1992, thank you for lifting us up on your big shoulders and joining us every year to celebrate the original bourbon barrel aged stout.

This year’s Proprietor’s explores the broad spectrum of chocolate. Using a combination of dark chocolate and two types of cocoa nibs, this rich and decadent beer highlights the whole range of chocolate from smooth and silky milk chocolate flavors to deep and earthy dark chocolate.

beer.beer_name: Bourbon County Brand Bramble Rye Stout (2018)
beer.beer_description: For this variant we aged Bourbon County Stout in rye whiskey barrels, then added raspberry and blackberry juice and puree from Michigan and Washington. The process resulted in complex jammy fruit notes that are prominent but well integrated with the caramel and chocolate flavors of the beer and spicy rye character from the barrels.
Strong Ale aged in Bourbon Barrels

A ridable American Wheat Ale boasting wheatey
nuts & juicy Motueka hop bolts. The deliverer of this truth: Akari Shogun, He who harnesses light will usher this summer force into your life.

Inspired by the juicy berries we grow on our farm each summer, Traffic Jam is the perfect balance of ripe sweetness with bold fruit aromatics.  Bursting with strawberries, blackberries, and raspberries, this semi-sweet captivates the nuance of our farm, in each and every taste.
Helping to resurrect your palette from the doldrums, Rise of the Angels bursts onto your tongue with a blast of grapefruit zest that is quickly followed by a parade of floral, citrus hops.
Spiked Hard Seltzer
With coffee, vanilla and notes of chocolate, this is a beer that really ties it all together. But, well, that’s just, like, our opinion, man.
Lush with bright fruit from the interplay of our house yeast and irresponsible levels of dry-hopping, Sun Fade quenches the dryness of the Southwestern desert like no other beer can.
Originally crafted in our two-car garage, we brewed this light-bodied sessional beer with dried lavender flowers and light caramel malt.
Imperial stout aged in bourbon barrels with cherries, cacao nibs and vanilla beans.
Hotbox Coffee Porter features cold-extracted coffee from Burundian and Ethiopian beans, to give the base porter flavors and aromas of dark plums, chocolate and hints of blueberry.

At 4.9% ABV and 35 IBUs, this drinkable IPA uses several varieties of hops to target the ever-evolving flavor. With tropical fruits, citrus juices, pineapple and spice berry up front in the aroma and flavor, the biscuit & toasted bread at the back balance out all the hops and make a great finish to go on to your next can of PINNER. It’s the perfect beer for a little sip, sip, give.

beer.beer_name: Henry's Hard Sparkling Water: Lemon Lime

beer.beer_description: A traditional Pilsner style beer with a big hoppy flavour and bite owing to dry hopping late in the brewing process. The zesty and fragrant hops make for a refreshingly dry finish and a slight sweet and sharp zing to the palate, which are best enjoyed with rich, creamy foods like pork sausage and mustard mash, quality fish and chips or cheese like Old Amsterdam, Edam or Brie. Grolsch is known to use a distinctively shaped bottle for its beer, known as de beugel or 'swingtop'.

Brewed with the Bloomington Chocolate Company, bony in color with a rich creamy head, sweet roasted flavors are balanced by crushed cacao beans added late in fermentation, giving way to a rich chocolate truffle finish.

Dos Equis Ambar (Amber) is a vienna style lager that was originally brewed by the German-born Mexican brewer Wilhelm Hasse  in 1897.

The brand was named "Siglo XX" ("20th century") to commemorate the arrival of the new century, and the bottles were marked with the Roman numerals "XX", or "Dos Equis" (two X).

brewery.brewery_name: Cervecería Cuauhtémoc Moctezuma S.A. de C.V.

beer.beer_description: This is the original Pabst Blue Ribbon Beer. Nature's choicest products provide its prized flavor. Only the finest of hops and grains are used. Selected as America's Best in 1893.

Double Dry-Hopped Double Oat Double India Pale Ale with Lactose — Made with Indiana Pilsner and oat malts, flaked oats, and a touch of lactose. Hopped extensively and repeatedly with a second helping of Citra, Simcoe, and Hallertauer Blanc. Ditch that diet. Indulge a bit! Summer is almost over, we can let those guts hang out. No more reason to worry about that beach bod.

Malt Bill: Indiana Pilsner & Oat Malt, and Flaked Oats with a Touch of Lactose
Hops: Citra, Simcoe, & Hallertauer Blanc
Yeast: CSB House Clean IPA Strain
Serving Temperature(F): 40-45 
Glassware: Tulip or snifter
Medium-bodied and copper-colored English-style special bitter with a noticeable malt flavor. Finishes with a hop bitterness and floral hop flavor.
Brown ale brewed with bourbon-soaked vanilla beans.

Firestone Walker Brewing has collaborated with Cigar City Brewing on Los Leñadores, an imperial brown ale aged in high rye bourbon barrels and infused with African and Brazilian hardwood spirals.

The featured hardwoods are African Padauk and Brazilian Amburana, sourced and created specifically for Los Leñadores by Richard Hobbs of The Barrel Mill in Avon, Minnesota. The Padauk provides notes of waffle cone and chocolate to the beer, while the Amburana layers in accents of cinnamon spice and vanilla. The base imperial brown ale was aged for nearly 12 months in high rye bourbon barrels acquired from Four Roses. An initial twist was the inclusion of Proximity malt in tandem with Simpson Golden Promise malt and Simpson Golden Naked oats.

Smooth talking, dark, and decadent-Imperialism goes digital. Aromas of roasted coffee and chocolate on the nose. With hints of pit fruits, chewy toffee, coffee, and dark chocolate on the palate. Finished late with American hops for a dash of bitterness.
American Milk Stout brewed with lactose then finished with s'mores flavorings. Brewed in collaboration with The Collective.

No season is as synonymous with beer as autumn, when the most storied beer festival of them all, Oktoberfest, takes place in Munich, Germany. Since 1810, this celebration of good food, good company, and, most importantly, good beer, has most prominently featured Marzen-style lager–so much so that many refer to the beer simply as Oktoberfest.
Our Oktoberfest is a traditional Bavarian lager featuring all-German malts and rare German hops. This dedication to authenticity produces a beer that would be as at home in Munich as it is here in the Midwest United States. The aroma is authentic, the taste sweet and malty, and the finish crisp and hoppy; perfect for a beautiful fall day!
Saint Archer Gold is a light-bodied, flavorful yet refreshing light lager brewed in the tradition of Helles lagers, with just 95 calories and 2.6 grams of carbs.
Bursting with tropical aromas and juicy fruit flavors from Mosaic and Amarillo hops, this golden IPA is perfectly bitter with a refreshing, sublime finish.
This Belgian - style Dark Strong Ale is full-bodied with rich, complex malt character balanced by fruity esters from Belgian yeast.
Fruited American Sour w/Peaches
Chocolate stout featuring bold cocoa up front with a light touch of coffee in a decadent full bodied finish
Ancho, Anaheim, and Serrano Chile peppers replace the hops in this Amber infusion.

Pilgrim's Dole is a barleywine-style ale made with fifty percent wheat malt, or what we at New Holland call a wheatwine. Pilgrim's Dole blends warming and slightly sweet flavors with a unique caramelized character. Rich, malty body with unique caramelized character and hints of raisins, nuts and figs. Pairings: fruit crisps, creme brulee, salted caramels, slow-roasted meats.

How do you improve upon legend? A few years ago, our brewers were tackling this very question. Taking our beloved Dragon’s Milk, they ramped it up in every way to create something even bigger and bolder. After three separate mashes, a delicate lautering, and a year’s slumber in New Holland Spirits barrels, Dragon’s Milk Triple Mash was born. The rest, as they say, is history.
Waves of blueberries from Michigan’s West Coast crash onto the shores of earthy, floral and fruity Mosaic hops. Sit back, relax and soak up this crisp golden ale.

beer.beer_name: Dragon's Milk Reserve: Coconut Rum Barrel
beer.beer_description: Coconut complements the roasted chocolate flavor of Dragon's Milk, coaxing flavors that are reminiscent of lazy summer days. Rum barrels add a tropical character.

Dragon’s Milk White is a nod to New Holland Brewing’s 20 years of barrel-aging expertise and commitment to innovation in the name of flavor. The next legend to unfold in the Dragon’s Milk family, Dragon’s Milk White creates a full flavored, yet lighter stout drinking experience that presents familiar flavors in a completely unexpected way.

Mad Hatter’s whimsy is celebrated with floral aromatics from assertive dry-hopping, and a bright, hoppy body, punctuated with Centennial, Citra and Michigan-grown Cascade hops. Citrus and pleasant bitterness excite your palate before welcoming a balancing finish.
Hoptronix 1-ups the game with its galactic bitterness. Mosaic hops give this IPA a dank aroma, yet it finishes smooth and crisp.

Tangerine Space Machine is a New England style IPA, it's nose is huge with tangerine and a little hop in the background. The mouth feel is juicy and full bodied. The flavor is citrus, fruit and subtle bitterness with comes from a blend of Galaxy, Topaz and Michigan Copper hops.
Rose ale brewed with passion fruit, raspberry, and apple.

Famous for its rich amber color and medium-bodied flavor with roasted caramel malt for a subtle sweetness and a combination of cluster and cascade hops, this true original delivers a well-balanced taste with very distinct character. Born from a historic recipe that was resurrected in 1987, Yuengling Traditional Lager is a true classic.

Learn more: http://www.yuengling.com/lager

Best enjoyed by a crackling fire, this decadent, pitch-black stout swirls with cheerful winter flavors. The tan head wafts of vanilla, bourbon, molasses and espresso notes, finiahing in a crescendo of chewy anise.
Dry with a floral, gin-like bent, Botanical is a cider spiced with juniper, lemon myrtle, coriander & cardamom.
A dry, effervescent cider with a twist. Infusions of lemongrass and ginger give way to nimble notes of apple and pear.

Musing on our bright and frisky Peach Dodo, this nitro nocturne is suffused with a healthy dose of vanilla and lactose. The result is a tart and silky reverie revealing notes of luscious peach cobbler, vanilla cream and soft spice. 

For the full nitro experience, shake the can, crack open slowly, then pour straight down into a pint glass!
Strawberries, vanilla, and lactose in the key of nitro. The result is a silky sonata ringing with notes of tart berries and fresh cream. Go ahead, try it. Strozzberry tastes like...strozzberries.

Raspberry Blondie is the latest entry in our Brewers’ Series, a collection of specialty beers concepted by individual members of our brew team. Brazillian coffee beans from Deeper Roots impart notes of stone fruit and dark chocolate, complementing fresh additions of raspberry and cacao nibs. Bright in color with deep, complex flavors, Raspberry Blondie is a limited, draft-only release.

This single hopped pale ale detonates upon the palate with a brilliant array of dank, tropical fruit, grapefruit blossom, mandarin orange and blueberries. Golden Promise malt provides a clean base- a kaleidoscope of flavor delivered with the simplest of recipes.
NE Milkshake brewed with El Dorado, Centennial, Vanilla, blackberry and Raspberry
A nice smooth porter with a back end of peanut butter happiness.

The Duncan Clan is named in honor of our Scottish side of the family, including Uncle Jack. This dark beer features rich, malty flavors of caramel and toffee balanced by roastiness and a subtle rye spiciness. This style is all about featuring the malt, leaving a very subtle hop presence.

In honor of Uncle Jack’s nickname for his niece, Molly, seemed fitting for this rich, milk stout. Like a chocolate milkshake without the straw, it features chocolate and coffee notes, and almost chewy thanks to the addition of lactose and flaked oats. This beer boasts a bronze medal from the 2017 Denver Beer Competition and GOLD in the US Open Beer Championship.
Barrel Aged tropical sour ale. A melange of tropical fruits, over a year aged in neutral oak wine barrels, and with our house lactobacillus and brettanomyces bruxellensis.
This Midwest Fruit Tart Ale is brewed with 1,500lbs of Pink Guava, 500lbs of  Banana, and 400lbs of passion fruit per 30bbl batch.
Apricot Midwest Fruit Tart. 3,000lbs of apricots per 30bbl batch.

Rich with flavors of black forest cake, espresso and decadent fudge, this deeply dark Russian Imperial stout was brewed with cocoa nibs and raspberries, and aged on heaps of Madagascar vanilla beans. The beer's tart berries and vanilla smoothness elevate it to almost dessert-like levels. How can we best describe it? - Its a glass of comforting deliciousness!

Imperial Milk Stout — Rising from the Underworld, this Imperial Stout is loaded with milk sugar & oats.

Malt Bill: Indiana Malted Barley & Oats
Hops: Cascade
Yeast: CSB House Clean Strain
Serving Temperature(F): 45-50
Glassware: Tulip or snifter

Mischief is a hoppy Belgian-style golden strong ale. This wickedly good golden ale is fiendishly dry-hopped with American hops to add a layer of complexity and mystery to its fruity, dry Belgian-style character. Citrus and resin diabolically combine with ripe melon, pear and slight peppery spice in a precariously effervescent mixture. Enjoy it, but you’ll want to keep an eye out.
Older pale ale lager.

Tropical aromas of Passion fruit, Orange
and Guava dominate the nose while a big 
juicy hop flavor and smooth bitterness
complement the balance of the beer.
This Killer IPA earns its name by using six different types of hops while still remaining an aggressive well balanced beer.
A luxurious, warming barleywine rich with aromatic hops and dark, candied fruit character that hides its epic strength masterfully.

Dragon’s Milk Reserve: Maple Oak is the first of the Reserve series to receive the double barrel treatment, aging in both Kentucky bourbon barrels and bourbon barrels that previously held Vermont maple syrup. Our signature stout was also brewed with pure maple syrup for the first time ever, providing a delectably sweet complement to notes of roasted malt, vanilla, and oak.

Annual collaboration release between Stone’s Greg Koch, Wil Wheaton, and Drew Curtis. Stout brewed with pecans & rye, one quarter aged in Bourbon barrels. Use as master listing. Each year has separate vintage listing; ABV may vary slightly depending on release year.
Belgian style oak aged dark ale, brewed with honey, dates, and raisins.
A dry-hopped, easy-drinking American IPA by the people, for the people (who happen to be our employee-owners!)
Our Dark Hero (A dark java milk stout) aged in a Tawny Port barrel, which has enhanced the chocolate notes that are already in Dark Hero and adds some rich vinous characteristics to it.
Imperial Stout infused with Ghost Peppers, the third hottest pepper on the planet. The goal is to find the perfect balance with respect to heat, pepper flavor and drinkability.

Complex malt flavor with a rich roasted aroma and a warming finish. 

“Good Times are Good Times, But a Hangover is Rough”

Availability: On draft & in 22oz. bombers at our brewery taproom & at select craft beer bars. Released in Jan/Feb.

beer.beer_name: Bourbon Barrel Aged Vanilla Mail Order Bride 2017 (Purple Wax, 1792)
beer.beer_description: A true russian imperial stout. chocolate and roast malts, hints of dark fruit and earthy hops create a truly great beer. this version is special. she was treated with an extra long voyage inside of the best bourbon barrels we could get our bare hands on. she soaked up complex notes of oak, vanilla, and fine bourbon to create a unique, drinkable stout for that special occasion.

"If you like Piña Coladas, and getting caught in the rain....." - Rupert Holmes.  This is the beer that you’ve looked for, come to the Moon and escape!  Pineapple and coconut prevail in this light American-style wheat beer.  Yum!

Unlock the Vault, our series committed to the careful, prolonged conditioning of barrel-aged ales. Claim a special Exemption, our abbey-style tripel ale with citrus peel and coriander. Wheat, oat and artisan malts contribute a smooth, malty body balanced by the smokey, vanilla notes of mezcal barrels.

Chocolate Coconut Milk Stout — Hopped with Galena supported by pale, crystal, caramunich, roasted barley, special b, black malts with oats & chocolate giving way to dark opaque liquid Mounds Bar. (contains lactose)
Imperial Milk Stout brewed wifh lactose, coconut, vanilla, and chocolate
"Mom make me a sammie!" she yells back, "It's peanut butter jelly time!" Sammie is a blonde ale brewed with unmalted wheat, lactose, Concord grape juice and peanut butter. A PB&J in a glass.
We aged a portion of this hearty Scotch ale in a port barrel and blended it back into the base.  The result is a complex brew with distinctive flavors of port wine and milk chocolate.
Soviet Occupation brewed with Coconut, dark roast coffee, and vanilla.

This beer is a dark cherry variant of our Edison Imperial Stout. As with the base beer, this was released as a sneak peak at our Wabash taproom at the Second Annual Electrification Day Brew Bash. The base beer is named after Thomas Edison, and this variant is named after his second child, Thomas, Jr., who was nicknamed Dash.
We left the main line with this dark brew. Notes of cocoa, anise, and fig.
Rich and complex, this robust flavored stout hits you with a smooth and roasty-burnt malt start and a hit of chocolate. Don't be fooled by the high ABV, this beer is creamy dessert brew.

When your tastebuds beg for a pounding this IIPA sneaks up with smoothness, and then: Bam! Citrus uppercut! Biff! Dank bitterness! Wham! A piney bite! Ooof! Floral, dank pine and citrus aromas! Kablam! 8.2% ABV! Sha-boom!
We use white wine varietal grapes and add a hint of strawberry that make this a perfect beer/wine hybrid for everyone to enjoy.  Okurrrrr!
Champagne-like with a tartness and extra effervescence. Thirst quenching ale with farmhouse qualities

beer.beer_name: TIKI Sour Ale: Tequila Barrel Lime
beer.beer_description: Our famous key lime sour aged in tequila barrels.
An American Pale Ale brewed with Cascade hops and a huge addition of Blood Orange.

When brewery founders Dan, Dan and Dave decided to brew a Belgian Tripel the only logical name was Tripel D. This beer is also a triple threat as the malt, hops and yeast each impart characteristics that blend together to form a smooth beer.
Soda Pop IPA brewed with raspberries, blueberry juice and lactose

This Strawberry Milkshake IPA tastes like a jar of our Grandma’s homemade jam: perfectly sweet, tart and delicious. We’ve used vanilla beans, lactose sugars and 126 lbs of strawberry puree (for a 2-barrel batch) to create a balanced, refreshing Milkshake IPA that starts sweet and ends with fruited tartness and a very mild hop bitterness. Cheers!
Made with variety of eight hops, this hazy, juicy beer provides a major punch of citrus flavor. *Gold medal winner at the 2019 Indiana Brewer's Cup.

Named in honor of the Indianapolis 500 winners' tradition of chugging milk at the finish line, this milk stout offers a rich malty and chocolate flavor from a mix of six different malts. Lactose provides a desired creaminess and fullness to this drinkable, refreshing beer.  *Gold medal winner at the 2019 Indiana Brewer's Cup.
A smooth, dark lager with hints roasted malt and German Tettnang hops.
Mid 2019 release imperial stout with peanut butter. Batch 3 was released in bottles & on draft 5/9/19.
No. 52 in Barrel-Aged Series: STOUT AGED IN BOURBON AND MAPLE SYRUP BARRELS WITH MAPLE SYRUP, COFFEE, AND CINNAMON

Bud Light is brewed using a blend of premium aroma hop varieties, both American-grown and imported, and a combination of barley malts and rice. Its superior drinkability and refreshing flavor makes it the world’s favorite light beer.

Jai Alai, a game native to the Basque region of Spain, is played on a court called a fronton. Jai Alai players attempt to catch a ball using a curved mitt whilst the ball travels at speeds up to 188mph! Proving they have a sense of humor the Spanish dubbed this game, with its ball traveling at race car speeds, “the merry game.” Tampa was once home to a bustling Jai Alai fronton but sadly all that remains of Jai Alai in the Tampa Bay area is this India Pale Ale that we brew in tribute to the merry game. The India Pale Ale style of beer has its roots in the ales sent from England to thirsty British troops in India during the 18th century. Pair Jai Alai India Pale Ale with beef empanadas, deviled crabs, and other spicy dishes.

Big Wave is light golden ale with a subtle fruitiness and delicate hop aroma. A smooth, easy drinking refreshing ale. The lightly roasted honey malt contributes to the golden hue of this beer and also gives a slight sweetness that is balanced out by our special blend of hops.

For those Qualified, our abbey style quadrupel. This strong, dark ale features Belgian specialty malts with rich, deep notes of raisin and plum, enhanced by dynamic Belgian esters. A sweet, complex ale, it’s the perfect dessert beer to sip and savor.

Don't be exempt from Triple Hopped Exemption, our citrus forward Belgian-style tripel featuring El Dorado, Pacific Gem and Citra hops. A robust bouquet of floral and tropical fruit notes are complemented by flavorful Belgian yeast esters. Enjoy fresh - there's no extension on this special once-a-year-release.

beer.beer_name: Smokin' on the Dock of the Bay

beer.beer_description:
Let's dispel the myths first... Recipe from medieval times? No. Stolen DNA from a castle? No. Brewed by a wizard? Maybe. The Sorcerer casts a spell upon your senses with complex malt, dried fruit, raisins, figs, plums, spice cake and a wonderful Belgian candi sugar sweetness.

Food Pairings: Steak, Goose, Apple Pie.

BEGINNING GRAVITY: 20.0 Plato

ENDING GRAVITY: 3.3 Plato   COLOR: Ruby Red

YEAST: Belgian Special Blend  

HOPS: German Perle, Czech Saaz

MALT: Pale, Pilsner Malz, Munich, Dark Munich, Aromatic, CaraAroma, Carafa

You stand out in a crowd and only need one leg to find balance. You’re not afraid to get your feet wet and you don’t give a flock what others think. You embrace your inner flamingo and dare to turn your dreams into reality. You’re ready for pink beer. Flamingo Dreams is a refreshing change from the ordinary with a berry burst, frisky zing, and a nitro glide that’ll bring out your vibrant side. Join the flock and let’s flamingle.
Espresso Infused Black Raspberry Mead - ​heady coffee aromas meet up with big berry flavor, combining to create a note of chocolate, finishing clean with a hint of coffee.
Pineapple and habenero!

Blackbeard's Breakfast is a robust porter with a new world twist. Aged in bourbon barrels and brewed with Chesapeake Bay Roasting Company's Dark Sumatra coffee, this porter is flavorful and complex. Featuring unique English malts, this brew will have strong notes of caramel and a slight nut character. Paired with bourbon notes and the sumptuous Sumatran Coffee, Blackbeard's breakfast will please coffee and beer connoisseurs alike.

The CPA accounts for it all. This 8.5% alc/vol imperial golden ale excels in refreshment featuring sweet, ripe peach notes with a creamy, rich body and smooth finish. a certified original, the CPA is au-dit it can be in what can sometimes be a-ccrual world.

Coors Light is Coors Brewing Company's largest-selling brand and the fourth best-selling beer in the U.S. Introduced in 1978, Coors Light has been a favorite in delivering the ultimate in cold refreshment for more than 25 years. The simple, silver-toned can caught people's attention and the brew became nicknamed the \Silver Bullet\" as sales climbed."
Welcome to flavor country. This Pale Ale has just the right malt backbone to support an explosive juicy hop profile. Derived from a new blend of proprietary hops. We hope you’ll enjoy it. Cheers!
Corona Extra Mexican Beer is a crisp, clean and well balanced cerveza with fruity-honey aromas and a touch of malt, making it a great tailgating beer, beach drink or barbecue refreshment.
Wheatwine featuring the Two Brothers original Hefeweizen recipe taken to new heights with a higher strength and an aromatic finish.
This Beer is Not to be a Fruity Beer. Only to have a very slight nose and Taste of Blueberries..2nd test batch for amount of Blueberries
Moderately bitter front and finish.  Slightly sweet, full flavor but well balanced.
Combination of Milk, Coffee and Chocolate,a well rounded taste sensory pallet will pick up on a slight Milk to sweet flavor, than a mild chocolate to hint of Coffee.

Our signature bourbon barrel-aged stout paired with a refreshing blend of raspberry and hibiscus, lending fruity tartness that enhances the underlying flavors of bourbon, vanilla, and roasted malt character.
Blueberry/Blackberry/Raspberry Roselle
Giantsbane is a Double Stout brewed with a complex amalgamation of dark and roasted malts. Black, roasty, and hefty.

Inspired by the classic "Hawaiian Blue" Tiki cocktail, this Tiki Style DIPA brewed w/ pineapple, tangerine, coconut, milk sugar, and raw cane sugar. Dry Hopped with Denali and cryo Sabro to amplify the tropical pineapple and coconut aromas and flavors.

An New England IPA that’s made ENTIRELY from oats and wheat.  Splendidly hazy with aromas of stonefruit, pineapple, and citrus. An insane amount of Citra and Denali hops per barrel make this beer an incredibly juicy and citrusy treat with an approachable level of bitterness.
An Oatmeal Milk Stout made with the addition of lactose to add a full body and mouthfeel. A dark, roasty ale with notes of chocolate and coffee. Served on Nitro
Borubon, vanilla, cranberry, cinnamon, coconut, caramel, clove, boozy
Fruity, melon, boozy, delicious
Rosé, kiss of pomegranate, hard and soft tannins, blend of Oregon apples, Haralson, McIntosh, pomegranate juice.

Cherry, hints of sweet/tart, dry tannin.
Apples: Connell Red, cortland, Dolgo Crabapple, Fireside, Haralson, Honeycrisp, Honeygold, Keepsake, mcIntosh, Regent, (Montmorency cherries from King Orchards in Michigan)

beer.beer_name: Contains Bees: Peanut Butter Honey Blonde
beer.beer_description: A refreshing blonde ale with creamy peanut butter and sweet Minnesota honey. Tastes better than an open-faced peanut butter sandwich on Wonder Bread. Bright honey flavors provided by the real bees of Minnesota's own Fieldstone Apiaries.
A pleasantly tart, floral, and drinkable saison. Brewed with hibiscus petals and aged on super fresh mangos for a juicy, tropical twist.

This dark-colored brew is deceptively sweet, chocolatey, and creamy. It’s refreshing enough to enjoy in the summer and
heavy enough to thicken your blood for a Minnesota winter.

A Milkshake IPA made with Super Galena hops plus lactose, orange, and vanilla. Tastes mostly like an orange creamsicle, but it's also a beer. The brew house is a little ol' place where we can drink together.

(We Want the Funk Series) This Berliner weisse has a sharp sourness balanced by addition of lots of red raspberry, cherry, and blueberries. It has a light body with a some what dry finish. With it's low ABV and addition of fruit it will leave you refreshed.

Like the young fox it was named for, this copper-colored Kupfer is brewed with a lively spirit. With a distinct peachy flavor and a light body, our Kupfer is a cheerful, easy-drinking addition to any hike or campsite, perfect for watching the sunset or capping off an evening. And, just like real kits, when you see one, there’s usually a few more around.
Brewed with orange juice,, orange peel, coriander and grains of paradise.
A part of the Keep It Simple Series, this simple ale with complex flavors focuses on quality Pilsner malt, Citra Hops and an unique saison yeast strain.

Brewed with white and flaked wheat and American two-row barley, Persephone perfectly balances wheat malt and pomegranate tartness for a truly refreshing beer.  If you don’t think you like beer, give her a try, we bet you’ll change your mind.
Chock full of blueberries & raspberries for a juicy complement to Pebbles, our Midwest IPA.

This long time favorite makes a long-awaited return to the Bourbon County Stout roster. Utilizing whole grade A vanilla beans from Madagascar, Vanilla delivers on all the quintessential things fans love about this variant: aromatic vanilla, marshmallow, toffee, oak, and floral notes highlighting the creamy mouthfeel and enhancing the chocolate flavors that are ingrained in Bourbon County Stout.
Already a Fun Size treat, we added loads of Tugboat Coffee to our Milk Stout with peanut, vanilla bean, cocoa nib, and sea salt. The best part of waking up is the Fun Size in your cup!
Pleasing malt notes of biscuit and honey, coupled with delicate floral and citrus aromas, make this an easy drinking golden ale that is friendly to everyone's palate.

Our rosé cider is a blend of hand-pressed heirloom Michigan apples aged in French oak barrels. It is truly cider make like wine with floral notes and a dry, crisp finish.
Rosé pours with the light pink of spring apple blossoms, with bright floral notes and hints of fresh-picked apple, grapefruit peel, and green strawberry. The finish is clean with just a slight tartness.
The Bomb! that we all know and love, with the addition of Christmas spices – cinnamon, ginger, and nutmeg.

A German-style Ale that is fermented at cooler temperatures to provide a crisp, clean, taste.  Our Kölsch is hopped with German noble hops to provide a spicy, herbal aroma that quickly gives way to the soft sweet aroma and flavor from the use of Pilsen and Wheat malts.  This beer is perfect for those wanting a lighter, refreshing beer to enjoy out in the yard or at a game.

Our flagship IPA epitomizes the balance of a Midwest IPA. Dry-hopping with Citra and Simcoe creates intense tropical and citrus aromas, while the strong malt bill produces an excellent balance with the hops for a smooth and minimally bitter finish.
Hell is German for "light." A pale gold lager with bready malt aromas and flavors, floral hop aroma, and a balanced finish.

Papaya, mango, and stone fruit waft in a cloud above a brilliantly glowing orange cylinder of citrus and vanilla. A hint of dank bitterness follows into the darkness. Gather your forces, brave the journey, and recognize the true ruler of Arnor.
A sour and spicy gose brewed with heaven facing chili peppers, fresh ginger, and a pinch of sea salt. Tart aromas of citrus and ginger, a spicy twist on the palate, and a crisp and dry finish.

A hazy and intensely dry-hopped Northeast-style IPA that's all about the fresh, unfiltered aroma. Pull it in close and drown your nose in a juicy spill of tangerine, peach, guava, and mango. With a pillowy-soft mouthfeel and light bitterness, this beer goes down surprisingly easy for a hop-bomb.

*Gold Medal, International Beer Cup 
& Brussels Beer Challenge, 2017

A full-flavored American Pale Ale for the Beijing working man. Pronounced notes of grapefruit and pine resin greet the palate, with moderate hop bitterness supported by a backbone of pale and specialty malts.

A Belgian Wit, Beijing-style. Pours hazy yellow with plenty of fluffy white head and bright aromas of mandarin orange and coriander seed. On the palate, the mild sweetness of the light grains blend with notes of earthy spice and fresh citrus, ending with a zesty dry finish.

Brewer's yeast comes to grips with its wild cousin Brett in this modern take on a Belgian Pale Ale. This beer was dry-hopped with a blend of old-world and new-world hops, so give your glass a swirl and enjoy rich tangerine and tropical fruit aromas bursting out from the grassy base notes.
Our year-round stout seduces with a decadent bouquet of bourbon-soaked vanilla beans. Velvety-smooth flavors of chocolate and coffee lead on to a touch of roasted malt bitterness in a lasting finish.

A revolution is brewing! Gaige Kaifang refers to "Reform and Opening Up", the program of economic reform that China initiated in the late 1970s. Inspired by the breakneck growth and development of Chinese craft beer, we brewed this unfiltered Triple IPA to reform your palate and open up your mind to new hoppy possibilities. Pale gold with notes of bitter orange marmalade, grapefruit peel, black pepper and licorice. On the palate, resinous hops and a spicy bite of alcohol rule over the rich and chewy malt.

This cloudy straw-colored ale was soured with lactobacillus and infused with loads of juicy Chinese Lychees. The enticing flavor of white peach and lychee is balanced by a refreshing tartness and a sparkling, semi-sweet finish.
Another beer from this German brewhouse
A German style brew house in Beijing
Served in a gold label-bottle. Brewed in Shanghai.

Bomb! is an imperial stout aged on Nordaggio's espresso beans, chocolate, vanilla beans, and ancho chile peppers. All the flavors meld to create a truly unique beer. The peppers add just the right amount of heat to complement the intense coffee and chocolate flavors.

Fruli is a high quality Belgian white beer blended with pure fruit juice. The strawberry juice compliments the zesty fruitiness of the wheat beer and the result is a natural, soft and refreshing drink that is simply delicious!

Tsingtao Pure Draft is a smooth, crisp and light-tasting draft beer. It is brewed with domestically-grown hops, select barley, all-natural yeast and pure spring water from China’s Laoshan Mountains. Tsingtao Pure Draft is brewed with an exclusive low temperature filtration process preserving the beer’s true flavor to create an incredibly refreshing beer-drinking experience. It is the perfect accompaniment to Pan-Asian cuisine and light appetizers.

Tsingtao Beer has a pleasant aroma and a well-balanced taste. It has high-malty flavor and well-hopped character. Tsingtao is produced with spring water from Laoshan, a mountain area famous throughout China for the purity of its water. The domestically-grown hops used to brew Tsingtao are of such high quality that they are also exported to European breweries. Tsingtao also uses the finest yeast and barley imported from Australia and Canada in its brewing process. 

Made partly with rice as an adjunct.

brewery.brewery_name: 强麦啤酒 Strong Ale Works

beer.beer_description: A sour brewed with Tibetan yak yogurt, puffed Tibetan highland barely, and butterfly pea flower.

brewery.brewery_name: 强麦啤酒 Strong Ale Works
强麦啤酒 Strong Ale Works

beer.beer_description: A moderately sour wheat beer, light, easy drinking, dry hopped with mosaic.

brewery.brewery_name: 强麦啤酒 Strong Ale Works

beer.beer_name: Cafe Pale Ale 咖啡馆啤酒

强麦啤酒 Strong Ale Works
强麦啤酒 Strong Ale Works

beer.beer_description: A golden ale with smoked malt.

brewery.brewery_name: 强麦啤酒 Strong Ale Works

beer.beer_description: The Tsingtao stout for the Chinese market (this one) is 3.0% weaker than the export one.
Raw beer available only direct from the Tsingtao Brewery in Qingdao, China, before final filtration and purification process to draft beer (纯生).
Pale lager with a carbonation. Has a light malty nose and lager taste.
Jujube flavour stout

beer.beer_name: Can I Ask You A Personal Question? (Strawberry Rhubarb)
beer.beer_description: Strawberry, rhubarb lemonade DIPA with milk sugar

beer.beer_name: Don’t Worry, My Mom Said It’s Cool
beer.beer_description: Imperial Birthday Cake Stout with Astronaut Ice Cream, Cacao Nibs & Vanilla

beer.beer_name: Who'd Like To Hold My Clipboard?
beer.beer_description: Double IPA brewed w/ our bois from Burial Brewing. Frappe Style DIPA with Tamarind, Vanilla, and Lactose.

Oubliette (\ˌü-blē-ˈet\) is a French term for a deep, dark forgotten dungeon devoid of light and hope. Our nearly opaque Imperial Stout is black as night with hints of plum at the edges and a rich tan head. Dark cocoa and roasted malt flavors are complimented by a lingering bitterness and a pleasingly warm alcohol glow.
Brewed as a collaboration with breweries from all over the city to celebrate Columbus Craft Beer Week. Featuring newly released Sabro hops and key lime puree.
A cyser style mead made with raw Ohio honey and fresh pressed Ohio  apples.
Blueberry mead aged two years and infused with chai spices from the North Market

Blueberry Sage is a blend of raw wildflower honey, blueberries, water and yeast. Fermentation removes most sugars, leaving the flavors of berries and honey. An infusion of sage produces layered flavors with a semi-dry finish.
Raw Ohio wildflower honey fermented with fresh Ohio sweet apple cider. Spiced with cinnamon, nutmeg & clove. Sweet
Raw Ohio wildflower honey fermented with water & infused with lavendar, chamomile, vanilla beans & ginger. Semi-sweet.
Wildflower honey with organic raspberries. semi - dry
Raw Ohio wildflower honey fermented with water aged on French & American Oak. Dry.
Raw Ohio wildflower honey fermented with water. Semi-dry.
Strong roasted malt character supported by the creamy sweetness of lactose added during the kettle boil. Available as a nitrogenated keg, which pushes the smoothness of the finish to the next level.

A Russian Imperial Stout with an intensely concentrated roasted malt character. Aggressively hopped to give it a resinous and herbal undertone.
IBUs: 50
Hops: Nugget, Falconers Flight
Malts: Pale, Roasted Barley, Black

Experience the magic of Purple Haze.® Clouds of real raspberries swirl in this tart and tantalizing lager inspired by the good spirits and dark mysteries of New Orleans. Brewed
with pilsner and wheat malts along with Vanguard hops, let the scent of berries in the hazy purple brew put a spell on you.

2017 Gold: Beer Army Beer Wars

2016 Silver Medal: Best of Craft Beer Awards

2015 Gold Medal winner: San Diego International Beer Competition

Canis Dirus, or "fearsome dog," is the scientific name for the Dire Wolf. One of the largest known breeds of wolf, the Dire Wolf went extinct at the end of the last ice age. Similarly, the Russian Imperial Stout was a beer style destined for extinction until craft brewers in America began to resurrect historical styles. Our Imperial Stout is named for the Dire Wolf because it is big, bold, and fearsome. Brewed with copious amounts of oats and brown sugar. Black as night with a dense tan head and chewy texture. Notes of dark chocolate, caramel, and espresso stand against a hefty bitterness to balance this monstrous beer.
Dire Wolf Imperial Stout aged on vanilla bean, cocoa nibs, cinnamon, chilis, and One Line coffee.
Dire Wolf infused with cinnamon and One Line Espresso.

That beer you like is going to come back in style...

The big, majestic Douglas Fir forests of the Pacific Northwest conceal many things: owls that aren't what they seem, supernatural intrigue, a lodge or two, delicious hops, and damn good coffee. This limited release Coffee IPA celebrates the return to the Great Northern by combining Pacific Gem, Cascade, and Citra hops from the region with locally roasted coffee from Bacca. The result is an aromatic beer that will leave you looking below the surface and beyond this realm.
A crisp, clean lager, inspired by traditional Belgian Pilsners.  This refreshing lager is brewed with Weyermann Pilsner malt and bittered with Czech Saaz Hops, to give it nuanced body and flavor.
Belgian style Stout: Dark stout blended with fruity belgian esters. Cocoa, plum & dark cherries up front followed by smooth smoky chocolate with hints of molasses.
Black Saison: Complex aromas of roses and raspberry. flavors include dark candied fruit, caramel and mild tobacco. Finishes dry and roasty as a black coffee bean.
Belgian style Abbey Ale: Gold & bold. Full bodied slightly boozy, with flavors of sweet orange and strong spicy belgian character.

In the search for a beer that best suited for summer, the obvious emphasis should be on refreshment and few ingredients are more undeniably refreshing than citrus fruit. This led us to the inevitable citrus Saison. The combination of tangerine and lemon zest add a bright, thirst-quenching complexity to a lower gravity example of a classic Belgian Saison.
This barrel-aged version of our Executive Order Wheatwine is aged for 9 months in Four Roses barrels. The resultant nectar is malty sweet, with a lot of vanilla and dark fruit notes.
A highly drinkable Golden Ale steeped with hibiscus, resulting in a delicious summer ale with natural tartness and a slight pink hue.

Altruistic Liquidity blends two worlds: the IPA and Kettle Sour. Featuring Motueka and Sorachi Ace hops along with kettle-souring, this beer blends bitterness and tartness with classic citrus flavors for a slightly hazy, refreshing Mojito-like finish.

This year’s Bourbon County Stout, aged in a mix of Heaven Hill, Buffalo Trace, and Wild Turkey barrels, yields a rich, complex mouthfeel. Flavors of cocoa, fudge, vanilla, caramel, almond, plus leather and tobacco, permeate this beer and deepen with each sip. We’ve bottled Bourbon County Stout for 15 years and this year’s vintage is one that you will want to hold on to for years to come.
Crisp and clean malt profile easily quenches the thirst on a hot Chicago summer day.
This 5.9% medium-bodied IPA has an auburn color and carries the flavors of gold nectarines with the aromatics of white peaches.

beer.beer_name: Farmers Market Series: Pressed Asian Pear Saison

beer.beer_description: This 5.5% rice lager carries subtle notes of baked lychee and baked pineapple on the palate alongside the aromatics of lightly toasted jasmine rice within a light, effervescent body reminiscent of vintage champagne.
This 6.3% medium-bodied Saison carries the flavors of a lemon meringue pie alongside the aromatics of Meyer lemons. The resulting Saison has a pineapple color and a dry finish.

The inspiration behind this beer rests in the kitchen of our Tasting Room. We proudly serve a 12 Layer German Chocolate Cake and so desired to build a similar flavor and aromatic profile within this barrel aged beer. This 16.0% Imperial Stout, aged for 12 months in Kentucky Four Roses bourbon barrels, showcases that reminiscent of rich chocolate cake, toasted coconut, caramel and a graham cracker crust. The best part of this beer -- just like our cake -- is that while big on flavors and aromatics, the beer is lighter in body than one might expect. We welcome you to experience Moody Tongue's favorite pairing cake in the form of a beer -- and then let your tongue decide.
Good light tasting barley wine
Red India pale ale brewed with the weekend of People's Brewing on International Women's Day. Dry-hopped with Yakima Chief "Pink Boots Blend" of hops.

This Traditional German style Altbier is a smooth beer with a sweet complex malt character balanced with Santium hops.  Brewed with a blend of German Munich and pilsner malt, two Caramunich malts, and Carafa, this beer has a medium body and reddish golden color.  We think this beer is perfect to enjoy after a bicycle trip, so we release it in time for National Bike Month in May. People’s Brewing is recognized as a Bike Friendly Business by the League of American Bicyclists.

American Style India Pale Ale. American based malt, flaked barley, Carafoam, and crystal malt reault in an orange hue. Hopped with Mandarine Bavaria Hops giving this beer a citrus specifically tangerine flavor and aroma.

American style Imperial IPA. This strong and clean IIPA was brewed with almost 50 lb of hops, spread out from the bittering side to the aroma additions. We used Summit, Citra, and Huell Melon. German Huell Melon adds a melon aroma to the otherwise citrus and tropical hop character. This beer was brewed in remembrance of the late Abel, our friend and colleague who worked for People’s Brewing for over 5 years.

American Style Double India Pale Ale with a huge citrus hop flavor.  We used American base malt with a very small addition of Crystal malts to give this a light-golden hue.  Additions of Summit, Galaxy, and 7C’s hops lend grapefruit flavors with hints of pine and pineapple.  Space Cowboy IIPA is extremely hoppy and higher in alcohol than a typical IPA. This batch has blood orange added post-fermentation. 
Take a ride on the galactic rodeo.

Brewed with American base malt and crystal malt for a light-golden hue and a citrus hop flavor.  Additions of Summit, Galaxy, and 7Cs hops lend grapefruit flavors with hints of pine and pineapple.  Take a ride on the galactic rodeo! This beer is not meant to be aged.

American Style White India Pale Ale. Brewed with American 2 row malt, 6 row malt, 22% malted wheat, and flaked barley, resulting in a light straw color. Galena and late Chinook hop additions result in an aggressive hop character with a big nose. Clean IPA with grapefruit and tropical flavors, forward aromas, and light but balanced body.
This hazy golden ale features bold hop flavors of grapefruit and orange from the use of cryogenic Amarillo hops.  Crisp and refreshing with a fruity, dry finish.
This brown porter was infused with organic coconut puree.  Flavors of toasted coconut and milk chocolate dominate this malty brew.
Named for a curious Purdue University event from the turn of the 19th century, this brew showcases bold bitterness and huge hop flavor with a bit of alcohol warmth.
This hearty brew features bold flavors of dark chocolate, dried fruits and coffee.  Alcohol warmth fades to a rich malty finish.

At Blake’s Hard Cider Co., we like spicing things up. That’s why we put dimmers on the lights in our Cider House. And it’s why we created this sweet, heated blend of habanero pepper, mango and our famous Blake’s apples. Experience a hard cider that’s really, honestly, truly like no other.
Experience El Chavo.

Chocolate Hazelnut Porter, or CHP as we call it, is a dessert in a glass. It is a rich, robust porter bursting with luscious chocolate and hazelnut. Notes of coffee and caramel round out this delicious treat.
Double Dry-hopped New England IPA with Mosaic hops
A big ole' dark beer filled with ethanol (and stone fruit esters).
Imperial stout brewed w/ graham flour, marshmallow, molasses, cocoa nibs & vanilla bean
Jasmine rice, Vienna malt, Bohemian togetherness.

A witches wheat! A pretty straight forward brew. A red ale with the additions of orange zest, chicory, roasted beets, rye and wheat. It is said that the first brewers were woman, and were later chastised as witches for creating these magical elixers (does NOT contain eye of newt)
Our American-style stout aged on organic vanilla beans.  Intense notes of coffee and dark chocolate lead way to subtle notes of natural vanilla.  Flaked oats generate a silky mouthfeel.
Our take on an American robust porter. Dark, thick, chewy, chocolaty, and of course, generously hopped.
Having a fresh palate will be the best way to enjoy the super subtle flavor of sterilized hemp seeds. Dry "hemped" with toasted seeds and hemp hearts.
Peanut Butter Milk Stout

Inspired by the Trappist brewers of Belgium, Monk Tears is a Belgian-style Quadrupel that has an earthy aroma of spice, dark fruit and caramel. The flavor starts off with a caramel sweetness followed by fruity date characteristics in the middle and finishes with fresh plum as you exhale. A mouthfeel that starts out thick and sweet but finishes with a slight dryness. Awarded a silver medal at the Best of Craft Beer Awards 2019 & 2020.

This Russian imperial stout has aromas of coffee, roast, & unsweet bakers chocolate. The alcohol in this beer is well hidden by the huge roasted malt character, bakers chocolate, slight malt sweetness and velvety smoothness.
Hazy gold, medium bodied malt backbone, bitterness with full tropical fruit overtones, passionfruit, mango, pineapple, white peach. Finished with brett for more fruit character and slight tartness.
New England Style IPA
A very smooth, chocolate colored milk stout with a sweet finish- and just the right amount of hops. Featuring 6

Brewed on International Women's Brew Day 2019 w/ our Tap Room Manager Amanda, this Brut Saison was brewed in honor of women around the world. Sara's Saison is a tribute to Sara Romweber (brewery family relative). Sara was an Indiana native & influential drummer in the 80's and 90's rock scene.
Dark yellow with light orange hints in color, with a moderate white head that lingers & laces nicely. Floral & spicy characters dominate the aroma. Notes of honey suckle, black pepper, clove, and orange peel. Dry with a gentle sweetness and mild spiciness, Sara's Saison has a mild persistent bitterness w/ lingering sweetness from the honey.
Semi sweet carbonated mead composed of peaches, blackberries, basswood honey and ginger.
It's peanut butter jelly time! This sweet mead leads off with a big smack of peanut butter before sliding into concord grape jelly notes. Long, long finish reminiscent of PB&J.
This sweet and very full bodied ale is good for any time of year here at the Brewpub. Mahogany in color with rich caramelized malt flavors predominating.
Schnitz's porter, with peanut butter flavor.
Chai, semi sweet, spiced cider
Collaboration with HopLore Brewing Company - Leesburg, IN. Kettle soured "cream" style ale brewed with lactose, vanilla then fermented and finished with raspberries. Creamy-fruity-juicy-tart.
Lyrical Poet is an Imperial Stout aged with chocolate and raspberries for 13-months in Tennessee whiskey barrels.

beer.beer_name: Game of Thrones: For the Throne
beer.beer_description: Golden ale co-fermented with Pinot Grigio and Viogner grape juice.
Stout with coffee added, aged in bourbon barrels
This rich, full bodied Belgian dark strong ale gives off flavors of fig, raisin, caramelized banana, chocolate, and warming, floral alcohol notes. Finished in bourbon barrels.

India Pale Ale originated when the British Empire was at its height. British soldiers and civil servants were stationed all over the globe (including India), and regular ales could not survive the long journey by sea to reach them. The British solved this terrible dilemma by adding excessive amounts of hops to their beer–using the preservative properties of hops to increase the life of their beers.
Our Dragonfly India Pale Ale is true to this tradition, featuring seven hop additions to create a powerful hop profile. A solid malt base, however, tempers the bitter American hops, giving Dragonfly a balance not often found in this style. The end product is a well-balanced, malty beer with the crisp taste of hops and an exceptionally floral nose

Upland Wheat Ale is a classic rendition of the Belgian Witbier (white beer) style. We brew it with organic coriander and orange zest to be light on the tongue and refreshingly tart. In the tradition of the Belgian Wit style, Upland Wheat Ale is unfiltered, allowing suspended yeast to create a cloudy, golden appearance and satisfying mouthfeel. Upland Wheat Ale is the flagship beer of our brewery and the best-selling beer brewed in Indiana.

A tart fruit beer brewed in collaboration with Function, Upland, Bloomington Brewing, and Switchyard. Locally sourced wheat malt and pilsner malt with a unique lactic acid producing yeast were used to make this beer. It was finished with over 1200 lbs of blueberries and pomegranates. Tart, fruity, and refreshing.

beer.beer_name: 20th Anniversary Encore Series: Stone 02.02.02 Vertical Epic Ale
beer.beer_description: In 2002 we began our groundbreaking, millennium-inspired series with Stone 02.02.02 Vertical Epic Ale. This bumped up Belgian-style wit—made all the more alluring thanks to an infusion of orange peel, coriander, a sprinkling of black pepper and a healthy dose of Centennial hops—was a bright way to begin this epic eleven-part vertical tasting.
Cedar Creek Brew Co Milk Stout made with vanilla bean puree

A moderately hazed, silky mouthfeel, citrus forward New England IPA with generous amounts of Citra, Amarillo, El Dorado, and Simcoe.  Huge aroma of oranges, tangerines and grapefruit with mild bitterness.

On the darkest day each year, we release our massive Bourbon Barrel Aged Russian Imperial Stout! Huge flavor notes of chocolate and coffee with a sweet bourbon accent and an incredibly smooth and full body makes this a truly unique beer that completely hides the formidable alcohol content!
A thundering hop presence collides with massive espresso and dark chocolate flavors in our dense and full-bodied imperial.
Russian Imperial Stout with roasted coconut, pecans, and cocoa nibs

Consistently delivered faster than any bottled or canned IPA on the planet, Stone Enjoy By IPA facilitated a paradigm shift in respect for and enjoyment of hoppy beers by ensuring craft beer fans the ultimate level of freshness. We brew this intense double IPA with more than 10 different hops, employing hop-bursting and dry-hopping techniques to amp up the peach and tropical fruit notes and overall hop factor. Brewed specifically NOT to last, this devastatingly fresh, golden beauty should be enjoyed within 37 days.

Classic American lager with a light body and pale gold color delivers crisp and thirst quenching flavors of mild grain, little to no hop, and subtle sweetness on the finish. An easy drinking American tradition.

This saison is pale straw in appearance with a long lasting white head. It has aromas of pineapple, funk, grass and lemon. The rye malt shows through in the flavor complimenting the spice from the saison yeast. The late noble hop additions shows through as earthy with a crisp dry Pineapple and lemon finish thanks to the brett.

This collaboration fruited sour ale was made with our friends from Mikkeller Brewing in San Diego. It represents a blending of our two programs featuring grapes from California chosen by Mikkeller and local grapes from Indiana. This sour ale is a blend of a 22-month Sour Brown and a 10-month Sour Quad aged in bourbon barrels. Next, it is aged on West Coast Malbec grapes and Midwest Chambourcin grapes. The resulting fruited sour ale is reddish brown in color and malt forward. Notes of grape, fig, citrus, and dried fruit embrace the senses with a dry and tart finish.

Barrel Chested Brewer’s Reserve is left in barrels for 11 months longer than standard Barrel Chested,
allowing the flavors to continue to blend and mellow. Upland brewers drove to Bardstown, KY to
personally pick up the Willett bourbon barrels for this beer and each bottle was packaged by hand.
‘Dirty Little Freak’ is our 5.8% coconut-caramel-chocolate brown ale that’s drinkably decadent, and slightly malty and with a gentle hop bite.

beer.beer_name: Bourbon Barrel Teddy Bear Kisses w/ Cacao & Orange Zest
beer.beer_description: Bourbon Barrel Aged Teddy Bear Kisses with cacao & orange zest

Ard Ri (pronounced Ard like hard and Ri like bee) means High King in Old World Gaelic and certainly lives up to its name. Like all Irish Red Ales, Ard Ri gets its distinct color from roasted barley used in the brewing process, but we’ve stepped up the malt and hops to make this imperial version of the style. Our signature St. Patrick’s Day brew is slightly sweet with a complex malt character, balanced by a large hop addition to make it perfect for the big beer lovers and hop heads alike.

I the undersigned do hereby pledge my undying thirst to this hoppy concoction of malt, water, and yeast.  By drinking this Double IPA, I agree that the contract is sealed, and Villain's fiendish deed shall be done.

Unlock the Vault, our series committed to the careful, prolonged conditioning of barrel-aged ales. Claim a special release Deduction dubbel aged in bourbon barrels and blended to feature smooth, sweet and complex notes of raisin, caramel and chocolate, enriched with toffee, vanilla and oak barrel character.

One of the earliest examples of the Russian Imperial Stout in the United States, Expedition Stout offers immensely complex flavors crafted specifically with vintage aging in mind, as its profile will continue to mature and develop over the years. A huge malt body is matched to a heady blend of chocolate, dark fruits, and other aromas. Intensely bitter in its early months, the flavors will slowly meld and grow in depth as the beer ages.
Everyone is sure to profit with In the Black, our limited-release, imperial dark saison with tangy blackberries and tart black currant.
Light in color and medium-bodied, but complex in flavor. Unique Belgian yeast imparts notes of white pepper, spice and sweet stone fruits.
Imperial Stout Aged on Vanilla
Imperial Stout Aged on Cacao Nibs
Imperial Stout Aged on Coffee
Imperial Stout Aged on Chili Peppers.
Brewed with coriander, mace, cardamom, grains of paradise and sweet orange peel, then aged in bourbon barrels for at least six months; this beer continues the Belgian tradition of spiced Noel ales.
A cherry grand cru aged in bourbon barrels
Traditional Belgian-style Quadrupel Ale.
Fresh picked blackberry aroma and flavor with a delicious cotton candy finish
Belgian strong brown brewed with kumquat.
Belgian strong brown showcasing the delicate balance of yeast character like banana and pear, and a delicious specialty malt richness.

We aged our imperial stout, Worthy Adversary, in a blend of Port and Madeira barrels for 26 months to create an extremely complex stout with intense flavors of cherry, plum, blackberry, & vanilla. This is quite possibly (probably) our most nuanced beer ever.
Gluten Free spiked seltzer.
Rum Barrel Aged Imperial Stout w/ Peanut Butter & Chocolate
A celebration in balance, this Scotch Ale has a strong malt presence and a hint of hops for a slight crispness and a smooth finish.

Our imperial stout, Worthy Adversary, sat in a blend of cognac & brandy barrels for 6 months to lend a smooth oak character and enhance the chocolate malt character while adding a touch of vanilla. What does this all mean to you? It means you should take your time and enjoy some of the subtleties of life with this one.
Porter Aged in Bourbon Barrels

“Say, ‘Hello,’ to our little friend,”
a seasonal collaboration with local
coffee roasters - Raspberry Ale Pacino
Mocaccino, a coffee, chocolate and
raspberry flavored milk-brown ale!
To paraphrase this ale’s namesake,
“Something would be missing
without the coffee.”

beer.beer_name: Wee Heavy Scotch Ale (2018) (Bourbon Barrel-Four Roses)
beer.beer_description:
Part of our "Waitin' On Wood Series," this Wee Heavy Scotch Ale was aged for seven (7) months in a first-use Four Roses Bourbon Barrel and features tasting notes of bourbon, dark fruit, brown sugar and caramel. 
12.2% ABV| 28 IBU’s

Join us for the tapping of this 70 Schilling Scotch Ale in honor of Bill and his kilt! The Kilt Bill Scotch Ale will tempt you with its fruity, sweet malt notes! 

4.5% ABV l 14 IBU's

This Dessert Stout features distinct notes of gooey, fire-roasted marshmallow and creamy, melt-in-your-mouth chocolate cloaked in crunchy graham cracker. A perfect pairing for campfire conversations and fun with friends! 	             6.75% ABV | 18 IBU’s

In August of 2018, we debuted three new Dessert Stouts and asked you to pick which one should be made again. The winner was this tasty S’mores Dessert Stout! Fast forward to November, 2018, and our S’mores Dessert Stout is here!! Just like you voted! Come enjoy it on draft and take some home in cans!

Formerly known as known as the Experimental Dessert Stout #3-S'mores. Then you told us you wanted more! so, we listened!

A huge, sweet Barley Wine with complex caramel malt notes, balanced by generous hopping and a high alcohol content. This fruity and malty beer is best enjoyed while keeping warm in the brutal winter months. January release

Day #1 of the 2017 12 Days of Milkshake Stout – More roasted notes than the  the original Milkshake Stout™ followed by sweet toasted marshmallow. Medium to full-bodied with no booziness. Toasted Marshmallow is a well balanced beer fit for any bon fire with no open flame or pointy sticks required.

The Juice is Loose.  Rochester Mills New England Style IPA was once a limited release but now is available year round.  Juicy tropical fruit aromas and flavors with a subdued bitterness have been achieved from a considerable amount of Citra and Mosaic hops added to this brew. Enjoy the Haze.
Penny', our newest Double Dry Hopped Double IPA was brewed with Lactose Sugar and nothing but Amarillo hops. Coming in at 8.2%, this DIPA packs some serious sweet grapefruit flavors and citrus notes.
Imperial white wheat stout with raspberries, cocoa nibs, vanilla and Hopscotch coffee. Silky with mild sweetness, full bodied and served on nitro for a sensual, creamy mouth-feel.

Over-the-top but surprisingly approachable, this twist on the classic style starts with several types of malted barley, rye, oats and wheat. Robust flavors of vanilla, espresso, whiskey, chocolate and roasted grain are balanced by hints of date and plum, with just enough hops to round it all out. Roughly one-third of the final blend is freshly brewed beer; the rest is aged for up to a year (or more!) in both first and second use whiskey casks.

Fans of the 12 Days of Milkshake Stout were especially fond of this one – pours a super dark brown with an off-white foamy head. Chocolate notes are more prominent than those found in the original Milkshake Stout™ mingling with rich, velvety cheesecake. Medium to full-bodied with no booziness. Chocolate Cheesecake is a well balanced beer that pairs nicely alongside a smoked brisket, beef barbecue or vanilla ice cream for a dessert.

Brewed with a blend of black tea,
turmeric, ginger, cardamom, star anise, and pepper this full bodied porter melds warm flavors of toasted vanilla and cinnamon roll.
A big, roasty stout blended with Ozo's organic coffee toddy.
This sweet, roasty beast of a RIS is brewed with cocao nibs, cinnamon, and vanilla. To this we added a TON of Rye Malt, giving it some very beautiful spicy notes.

Slightly sweet and full-bodied with hints of complex roasted malts and chocolate, Calfé delivers a kick to the corral. This pillowy, silky and aromatic Coffee Milk Stout is infused with java roasted locally by the team at Cincinnati's Deeper Roots Coffee - a multidimensional brew that delivers on rich, smooth and delicious.
Malt-forward amber with a sweet bread-like character and slight toasty flavor. Light additions of Cascade and Columbus hops give the slightest hint of citrusy bitterness.

Every good meal deserves a great beer.  That's why we are serving Meat & Potatoes with your dinner tonight.  We've cooked up a classic American Stout with a slight hop twist to stand up to the heartiest of meals.  Bold flavors of dark chocolate, coffee, and a hint of citrus drink in perfect harmony with robust foods.

No meat or potatoes were harmed in the brewing of this beer.
Bourbon barrel-aged sour, dark Belgian strong with elderberries
Bourbon barrel-aged imperial stout with raspberry & chocolate

​ Belgian yeast esters take center stage in this Belgian tripel, named after our owner's late 3-legged cat, "Speedy." Our brewers spiced this beauty with coriander and orange peel, then finished with Saaz hops for a spicy, yet floral complement to the Belgian yeast esters.
Dogfish Head’s Ancient Ale Kvasir revives hybrid Scandinavian grog. Tart hybrid beverage brewed with lingonberries, herbs, birch syrup.
Light and crisp and delicious. Clean finish. Cream ales are a uniquely American style.

Blue Moon Belgian White, Belgian-style wheat ale, is a refreshing, medium-bodied, unfiltered Belgian-style wheat ale spiced with fresh coriander and orange peel for a uniquely complex taste and an uncommonly smooth finish.
A Russian Imperial Stout with a hearty malt body and bold hop flavor.
A biting, bitter, tongue bruiser of an ale. With a name like Hopslam, what did you expect?

Our Barleywine Ale features American and Belgian malts which provide the base of this extraordinary ale. After 12 months in bourbon barrels the award-winning Straight Jacket emerges with notes of stone fruit, toasted coconut, molasses, and vanilla coming in waves as you swirl the glass.

Frozen Assets is a rich Belgian chocolate milk stout which features a generous amount of roasted barley, chocolate malt and lactose. Full-bodied with complex malt undertones, restrained hop notes, subtle Belgian spice and aged on cocoa nibs, Frozen Assets is a decadent treat on these cold winter nights.

The body of chocolate and coffee toasty malts with the appearance that of a blonde ale tells one they are drinking the White Stout Bigsby. Coco nibs from Davis Chocolate and cold brewed coffee and roasted beans from Zen Cafe help make this brew possible. Contains milk sugar.

Invest wisely in 401(Cake), our German-chocolate-cake-inspired brown ale featuring rich and sweet cocoa nibs, toasted coconut and Madagascar vanilla beans. Showcasing complex roasted and caramel notes, max out your contribution limit on this smooth dessert ale.
This stout is brewed with lactose (milk sugar) to impart a fuller body and sweeter palate.

We brew our continuously-hopped, Belgian-inspired Urban Wheat Ale with a blend of Belgian and American yeast. Dry-hopped with Citra – twice – striking a happy balance between the hop and grain builds with soft notes of lemon, coriander and ginger.  A naturally filtered Urban wheat Miss Ginger offers a nice, easy-to-drink session ale.
Brewed in the tradition of Trappist monks this rich, full bodied Belgian dark strong ale gives off flavors of fig, raisin, caramelized banana, chocolate, and warming, floral alcohol notes.
Bourbon barrel-aged stout with real banana and natural flavors.
Brugge's signature beer. Blackberries and lactobacillus.
Crisp, session West Coast IPA with lactose added. Initial malty sweetness gives way to bitter pine hop flavor and a creamy mouthfeel.

Bourbon BA Cider w/ Oak Chips and Cherries.
Blake's Ciderhouse/Winery and HopCat Exclusive!

Belgian strong ale aged in bourbon barrels letting the complexities of its malt composition perfectly marry with the nuances of oak and Kentucky. Pours Ruby red with citrus aroma, complex malt flavors and a slightly sweet and subtle bitter finish.
Imperial Stout brewed with Oreo Cookies.

Sweet Potato Stout, our original Sweet Potato Cream Stout, is the ideal Southern-style Stout. Brewed with roasted Southern-grown sweet potatoes, the background has an impressive taste with added notes of roasted chocolate, coffee, and caramel flavors with sweetening enhanced with lactose (milk sugar).

This crisp wheat beer has the aroma and flavor of fresh Louisiana blueberries. It’s brewed with pilsner and wheat malts and hopped with German Perle hops, then the juice from local blueberries is added to complement the toasty malt flavor. All our Harvest Series brews are made with the finest Louisiana-grown ingredients.

A perfect winter beer for curling up by the fireplace, this malt blanket features prominent toffee and caramel notes with just a hint of smoked malt. A subtle spiciness is provided by hopping with Magnum, Chinook and Styrian Goldings.

BJ’s Brewmaster’s Reserve™ is a line of proprietary craft beers made with premium ingredients and bolder taste profiles.  BJ’s Goliath™ Imperial Red Ale is brewed with six different malts and four varieties of hops. A big amber ale with intense hop and malt character for the giant in you. 

BJ’s Brewmaster’s Reserve. What our brewmasters drink.
Belgian inspired imperial stout aged in a dual purpose bourbon then sherry barrel

This full-bodied Imperial stout was aged for 4 months in a Heaven Hill bourbon barrel along with fresh vanilla. Robust malty sweet flavors up front move into a roasted malt character and accented by notable hop character. Roasty, rich & complex.

Aged in Bourbon Barrels: A Traditional brown, English-style Barleywine with complex malt sweetness of caramel and toffee. Full bodied with balanced bitterness and a warm finish.

Gold Medal, 2018 Beer Army Beer Wars
Bourbon Barrel aged Tap-O-Lantern.

A traditional English strong ale that has been aged for 3 months in a Four Roses bourbon barrel. It offers intense malty sweetness of caramel and raisin with a warming finish. Perfect for a cold, snowy day.

Blushing Monk is brewed with a ridiculous amount of raspberries and with a Belgian yeast strain that keeps our head cellar operator from sleeping for a week. It pours a stunning deep berry red and, at 9.2% ABV, has a surprising kick. The perfect dessert beer, it can be enjoyed on its own or paired with fresh cheeses, fruit, cakes and more.

beer.beer_name: Old Stock Ale Cellar Reserve Bourbon

beer.beer_description: Aged 12 months in bourbon barrels. This old man of a Barleywine comes a hollerin' with loads of toffee, caramel and hints of vanilla.

Welcome to the new world order. Our new Project stretches the limit of our brewing prowess. Crafted to be low calorie and gluten reduced this canvas showcases bright black cherry notes. Finishes light, crisp, and effervescent.

The next offering in our Barrel-Aged Program will have you reminiscing of campfires and ‘mallows. Overtones of vanilla, burnt sugar, and graham cracker give way to a smooth body and warming finish that’ll make you feel you’re right back next to that campfire.
A rich, dark stout with substantial alcohol warmness, notable roast flavors and hints of dark fruit and chocolate.

The brewery's most highly sought after beer, this imperial stout is aged to perfection in oak bourbon barrels. Look for this tasty treat to contain hints of bourbon and vanilla with roasted overtones that is sure to please any connoisseur's palate. Serve this beer at cellar temperature from a snifter glass, and enjoy this expression of our passion for brewing.
Deep, dark intense roasted malt, coffee and chocolate notes resound deeply in this imperial stout.

A big, roasty Imperial Stout with lactose and rye malt for body, brewed to celebrate the 2,000th batch from our production facility. European and U.S. caramel malts, coffee malt, and debittered roasted malt accentuate the toasted marshmallow and roasted flavors without acrid or burnt notes.
Sweet smoked malt combines with 200 pounds of local persimmons creating a medium bodied, orange colored, slightly sweet, slightly smoky Indiana beer.
Imperial American IPA, medium bodied, with robust hop flavors of mango, pine resin, pineapple, and bitter orange peel backed up against a sturdy malt backbone with a soft alcohol warmth.
